title: moist zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil and sugar.
Sift flour and cinnamon. Mix this into the egg mixture.
Stir in zucchini, vanilla and nuts. Bake
in 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: aloha cake
directions: Drain crushed pineapple.
Use juice in place of some of the water in the cake mix.
Bake cake in a 15 x 12-inch pan and let cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; cool and drain.
Cook onion in melted butter. Add mushroom soup and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Pour cheese mixture over broccoli.
Cook in oven at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spaghettios
directions: 1. Talk your dad into driving you over to Mammaw's house.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Cook noodles in chicken broth.
Melt butter.
Add chicken, pimento, soup, onion, milk and egg in large bowl.
Fold in noodles.
Pour into baking pan.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Pour butter over bread crumbs.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Mix with cheese and pineapple. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle crackers on top. Drizzle melted margarine on top of crackers.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: chicken pot pies
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bone.
Mix ingredients in a bowl. Take two deep dish pie crusts and bake until dry, not browned. Put ingredients in pie crusts and put regular pie crusts on top. Bake until top crusts are browned.
Makes two chicken pot pies.

title: one pan chewy granola bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix baking mix, oats, sugar, butter and egg in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan until moistened (mixture will be crumbly).
Stir in chocolate chips.
Press mixture evenly in pan.
Bake until center is set, about 15 to 17 minutes.
Cut into bars while warm.

title: passion punch
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and water in a large nonmetal pitcher or punch bowl.
Add ginger ale, ice or ice mold just before serving.
Stir to blend.
Makes 25 servings (4 ounces each).

title: country captain(my version of friccasied chicken and vegetables)
directions: Cut up chicken.
Rinse and place on paper towels to drain (2 wings, 2 legs, 2 thighs, 1 breast and 1 wishbone).
You can use 2 back pieces, if you like.
(I usually cook backs and giblets in water to use for dog food.)
Mix flour and Lawry's salt in plastic bag.
Dredge a few pieces of chicken at a time in the flour.
Heat oil in a large skillet; brown pieces of chicken.
Remove.
Add onion; cook until yellow.
Add celery.
Place chicken on top.
Add tomatoes with juice and prunes.
Cover.
Simmer for 35 to 40 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: penuchi
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Boil hard for 12 minutes. Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Beat until it thickens.
Add nuts if desired.
Cool and eat.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Pour into a greased and floured angel food cake pan. Bake at 300° until golden brown and firm.

title: chili
directions: In large pot, heat tomato juice and pork and beans. Lightly brown onions and bell pepper separately. Fry meat until brown; drain off grease. Add meat and other ingredients to juice. Simmer for a couple of hours.

title: pizza rice salad
directions: Prepare rice as directed on the package; cool.

title: chicken chili
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 3 quart saucepan, breaking up the tomatoes.
Heat to boiling point, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until chicken is white and the flavors are well blended.

title: farina torte
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients thoroughly, then fold in the beaten egg whites.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 40 minutes in a 350° oven. Cool, then crumble.
Put together in layers:
Cool Whip, then crumbs, Cool Whip and crumbs.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Decorate with maraschino cherries and walnuts. Refrigerate overnight.

title: frozen cheese pie
directions: Mix together.
Press into the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until brown. Cool.

title: onion soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Add onions and saute until transparent and golden.
Add consomme, two cans of water and the wine.
Simmer on very low heat until ready to serve.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add enough water to make paste. Beat in eggs, well beaten.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cool and pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain shrimp, rinse in cold water and let set in cold water for 15 minutes.
Mix together the rest of the ingredients and add shrimp last.
Be sure to squeeze the water out of shrimp before adding it to the dip.

title: basic seasoning for smoking chickens
directions: Mix thoroughly; store in a covered jar in a dry place.
Let it stand at least several days.
The longer the better before use. For a spicier taste, add 1 tablespoon nutmeg or 1 tablespoon of mace.

title: deer jerky
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Marinate the meat for 4 to 6 hours or overnight in covered dish in refrigerator.
Then drain. Place on dehydrator to dry for 8 hours.

title: black cows
directions: Scoop ice cream. Place one scoop into each of 4 tall glasses. Pour root beer over ice cream. Top with whipped cream.

title: lakeshore pecan praline cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour and nuts; mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly with fingers or fork.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Do not cook too long.
Makes 9 dozen.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Sift cocoa and sugar into bowl. Stir in bourbon, which has been mixed with syrup. Mix well; add crumbs and nuts. Mix well again. roll into small balls. Drop into powdered sugar; roll to coat. Allow to dry a day or so before using. Freezes well. Makes 3 dozen balls.

title: peanut butter crisp
directions: Mix cereal and peanuts; set aside.
Combine sugar and syrup. Cook to a full rolling boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour while hot over cereal mixture.
Stir gently to coat.
Pat evenly into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: *If in a hurry, 3 (tuna size) cans of white chunk chicken works great.

title: corn roast
directions: Let wood fire die down to glowing embers or glowing coals in charcoal grill.
Turn back husk and strip off silk from fresh corn.
Replace husks and lay ears on embers.
Keep turning and roast for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove husk and serve hot.

title: strawberry angel ribbon loaves
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake batter following package directions.
Divide equally between 2 ungreased 9 x 5
x 3-inch loaf pans.
Press batter with spatula into sides and bottom of pan to avoid air pockets.
Bake 30 minutes.
Suspend cakes, upside down with corners resting on 4 cans or glasses of equal height. Cool 30 minutes or pans cool to touch.
Split cake into 3 layers, lengthwise, using long serrated knife.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Mix cake as to directions.
While still warm, punch holes all over cake.
Pour over a mixture of cream of coconut and sweetened condensed milk.
Allow cake to cool thoroughly and spread with the Cool Whip, then sprinkle with shredded coconut.
Cake must be refrigerated and is very moist.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with onion according to directions on squash package, omitting salt.
Drain well, pressing between paper towels.
Combine squash mixture, mayonnaise, eggs, crackers, salad dressing mix and cheese in a lightly greased 2-quart shallow casserole dish.
Combine bread crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: ham ball
directions: *The small packages at Piggly Wiggly work real good.

title: sausage strata
directions: Trim crust off bread to fit Pyrex dish 10 x 6 1/2 inch. Brown sausage well. Stir in mustard. Spoon over bread and sprinkle with cheese. Combine ingredients and pour over. Set in refrigerator 12 hours. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Let set out of oven 15 minutes before serving.

title: crescent chicken roll-ups
directions: Cook chicken and cut into 1-inch pieces. Mix cream cheese, salt, milk and onions. Spoon mixture into separated, unbaked crescent rolls. Roll each one up with mixture inside. Brush top of rolls with margarine. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. For the sauce, mix sour cream and soup. Heat sauce on top of stove and spoon over rolls right before serving.

title: hungarian torte
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar until thick and lemon colored.
Add lemon juice.
Add walnuts and crumbs and mix well.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks (not too stiff or will be dry).
Fold whites into egg mixture.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice the sugar cookies on pizza pan.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes and cool.
Combine the cream cheese and sugar.
Spread on cooled cookie mixture.
Top with blueberry pie filling.
Top with various fruits.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: aunt susan's hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix well.
Pour into small casserole.
Heat at 350° until it bubbles, about 20 minutes.
Serve with low salt Wheat Thins and/or Triscuits.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large greased casserole, place tomatoes in bottom of pan.
In a mixing bowl, combine chicken a la king, milk, tomatoes or Ro-Tel, cheese, pimentos, bell peppers and onion and mix together.
Pour over tamales, sprinkling with potato chips.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: potato cheese puffs
directions: Chop onion fine.
Beat eggs.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until the blade of knife stuck in the center comes out clean.
Serve at once.
Makes six servings, about one cup each.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach; set aside.
Saute onion in margarine. Combine remaining ingredients in bowl; mix in onion and spinach. Refrigerate.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Can be frozen before or after baking.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar; beat until well blended.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in morsels and walnuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.
Makes one 9-inch pie.
Recipe may be doubled.
Bake 2 pies.
Freezes nicely.

title: cheese bars
directions: Open 1 can of rolls and spread to cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Sift flour with salt, baking powder and sugar.
Add milk; beat well.
Set aside.
Add spices and the almond extract to peaches. Set aside.
Melt butter in an 11 x 17-inch Pyrex dish.
Pour batter over butter (do not stir).
Pour peaches and juice over batter (do not stir).
Bake in preheated 350° oven until top is brown and crust rises to the top (approximately 30 to 40 minutes).
Remove from oven and sprinkle with sugar.
Return to oven and bake 10 minutes more.
Serves 8.

title: five-cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill at least 1 hour or overnight. For a "Six-Cup Salad," 1 cup drained fruit cocktail or 1 cup chopped pecans may be added.
Yield: 6-8 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Spread broccoli in bottom of a shallow baking dish.
Cover with chicken slices.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: creamy pineapple dessert
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve juice.
Add water to juice to make 2 cups liquid.
Combine pudding mix, gelatin and measured liquid in medium saucepan.
Cook, stirring over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Pour into a bowl and chill until thickened. Fold thawed topping into pudding mixture.
Meanwhile, combine cookie crumbs and melted butter.
Press into bottom and sides of 9-inch square pan.
Bake in 375° oven 8 minutes.
Cool.
Pour pudding mixture into cooled crust.
Top with pineapple tidbits. Chill about 2 hours until firm.
Serves 8.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Set aside.
Place apple in a medium size bowl; break egg over apple.
Add oil, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and nuts.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir dry mixture into apple mixture.
Spread in a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: barbeque sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add 1/2 cup water.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender (about 20 minutes); drain thoroughly.
Mix all the ingredients with carrots; serve warm or cold.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In a large pot, add all together.
Let cook slow for 1 hour, then test potatoes with a fork.
If potatoes are fully cooked, then it's ready to serve.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: hamburger "helper"
directions: Brown hamburger in large skillet.
Blend next 6 ingredients. When hamburger is brown, drain and mix dry ingredients with beef. Add the water and noodles.
Cook covered over medium heat approximately 10 to 12 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Serves 5 or 6. (One cup uncooked rice may be substituted for the noodles.) Cook 15 to 20 minutes.

title: butter toffee
directions: Combine sugar, butter, water and salt in saucepan.
Cook to 285°; stir occasionally.
Pour on buttered cookie sheet.
Cool. Spread with melted chocolate.
Cool.
Turn over and spread other side.
Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: kalaco beans
directions: Brown 1/4 pound bacon with 1 large onion.
Also brown 1 1/2 pounds hamburg and drain.
Mix and cook in slow cooker.

title: chicken gumbo soup
directions: Simmer chicken broth, onion, celery, beans, bouillon and pepper for 2 to 3 hours.
Add rice and additional water, tomato juice or V-8 juice as needed to prevent sticking.
Cook about 20 to 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally; add chicken, tomatoes and okra and heat thoroughly, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese chicken casserole
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package, except use 1/2 cup milk.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Spoon into 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Dredge chicken in flour and cook until brown.
Remove and keep warm.
Remove 1/2 of shortening.
Add onion, celery and pepper and brown.
Then add ketchup, water, Worcestershire sauce and brown sugar.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add chicken or pork.
Put in electric pan or 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes if in baking dish.
Simmer 1 hour if in electric pan.

title: quick chicken soup
directions: Put chicken broth in medium sauce pan.
Add pasta and simmer until pasta is tender,
about 10 - 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers or roll and butter.
Makes 2 - 3 bowls.

title: poulet de normandy
directions: Combine the first 2 ingredients and place half of it in a buttered 12 x 8-inch casserole.
Saute the onion and celery in 2 tablespoons butter. Combine this with the chicken, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Place in a casserole and cover with the remaining dressing mixture.
Beat the eggs slightly and add the milk.

Pour this over the casserole, then cover and refrigerate overnight. Remove from the refrigerator 1 hour before baking and spread mushroom soup over the casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: baked bananas
directions: Cut bananas lengthwise.
Put on cookie sheet and brush with butter.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Combine other ingredients and pour over bananas.
Bake another 15 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together in a large mixing bowl.
Add oil, eggs, pumpkin and soda water.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into 3 lightly greased and floured coffee cans or bread pans. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: santa's surprises
directions: Combine butter, peanut butter and sugars until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla until combined. Mix in flour, soda and salt. Cover and chill dough for 2 to 3 hours. Remove dough from refrigerator,

divide into 1-tablespoon pieces and flatten. Place a Snickers miniature in center of piece of dough. Form the dough into ball around each Snickers. Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes. Melt Dove chocolates and drizzle over top of each cookie.

title: broccoli chicken bake
directions: Place chicken and broccoli in layers with dressing in 2-quart casserole.
Mix soup and broth together well.
Pour over top. Add cheese slices on top when half baked.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie dessert
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and oleo.
Put in and pat down in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 10 minutes.
Mix balance of ingredients for filling and pour over baked crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until knife tip shows done.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread nuts in bottom.
Sprinkle coconut over pecans.
Pour prepared cake mix over pecans and coconut.
Melt margarine and cream cheese together.
Add powdered sugar and mix well.
Spoon mixture over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 24 squares.

title: biscuits and gravy
directions: Cook biscuits as per cooking instructions.
Crumble sausage and brown in frying pan.
When sausage is browned, add 1/4 cup flour; stir into sausage.
Add 2 cups milk.
Stir until thickened. Serve over biscuits.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine pineapple and pudding mix. Fold in Cool Whip and pecans; mix well. Chill at least 30 minutes. Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt 6 ounces of white chocolate and all of chips.
Stir in peanuts, marshmallows and cereal.
Pour onto greased 10-inch pizza pan.
Spread to even out top.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Top with cherries and melt remaining white chocolate and drizzle over pizza.
Chill before serving.

title: skillet cornbread
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Heat the lard in a 9-inch iron skillet over moderate heat until the lard has melted.
Set aside. Combine the cornmeal, flour, baking soda and salt in a mixing bowl. In another bowl, beat the egg lightly with a fork, then stir in buttermilk and the melted lard.
Pour the buttermilk mixture over the cornmeal mixture and stir together just until the batter is smooth.
Pour the batter into the prepared skillet.
Bake in the center of the oven for about 20 minutes or until the top of the bread is golden brown and the sides have begun to draw away.
Cut into wedges.

title: meat and potatoes dinner
directions: In medium saucepan, bring 2-inches salted water to boiling. Add potatoes; cook 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain; return to saucepan.
With electric mixer at high speed, beat until smooth. Beat in butter, savory, salt and pepper; cover and set aside.

title: cappuccino mix
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Store in airtight container.
To serve, add 3 tablespoons of mix to 6 ounces of hot water.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Stew chicken and remove skin and bones.
Place chicken in baking dish.
In medium saucepan, put broth and soup.
Heat until thin.
In a bowl, mix flour, butter and buttermilk.
Pour broth and soup mixture over chicken.
Spoon batter over chicken and bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Peas and carrots (optional).

title: layered strawberry cheesecake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and margarine. Press evenly into bottom of a 9-inch pan.
Combine water, eggs, cottage cheese, 1/2 cup sugar, dry milk, flour, lemon juice, vanilla and salt in an electric blender.
Process 1 minute or until smooth.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn off heat and leave in oven 1 hour.
Set aside to cool.

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar together.
Add strawberries, pineapple and nuts or coconut.
Add Cool Whip and freeze.

title: easy butterscotch candy
directions: Melt morsels (you
may	wish to use the microwave power level 5 for about
3 minutes).
Mix with peanut butter and add cornflakes.
Spoon onto
wax
paper
and allow to cool. Delicious!!

title: italian honey twists
directions: Measure flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into sifter. Sift into large bowl. Scald milk with butter in small saucepan. Stir into dry ingredients, add beaten eggs, lemon rind and oil of anise.
Mix to make stiff dough.
Knead until smooth on floured pastry board.
Roll out thin, a quarter at a time.
Cut into strips 3/4 x 4-inches.
Knot loosely.
Let stand 5 minutes to dry slightly.
Drop in deep fat heated to 375°.
Fry, turning once, or until golden.
Drain.
Cool.
Pile in a mound in serving dish. Drizzle with heated honey.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: cold veggie pizza snacks
directions: *Broccoli, carrots, radishes, mushrooms, cucumbers, seeded and drained cherry tomatoes, celery, red onion or any combination. Preheat oven using package directions on dough. Spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan or a baking sheet with vegetable oil spray. Pat dough over bottom of pan or pat into a 13 x 9-inch rectangle on baking sheet. Bake dough using package directions. Let stand until cool, 10 to 15 minutes. In a small bowl,
beat cream cheese and sour cream until smooth. Stir in salad dressing. Spread over crust. Arrange vegetables on top. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate until serving time.
To serve, cut into 20 squares.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place in 3-quart casserole layers of bread, meat and cheese. Beat eggs with the mustard, salt and milk.
Pour over casserole. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 325° to 350°.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Drizzle with glaze if desired.

title: sauerkraut-raisin drops
directions: In mixer bowl, beat the 3/4 cup butter or margarine and the brown sugar until fluffy.
Add the egg, the first 2 tablespoons of milk and the 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Melt butter over medium-low heat.
Stir in garlic and heat briefly.
Gradually add the cheese, stirring constantly with a wire whisk.
After the cheese is melted, very slowly add the half and half, continuing to stir with the wire whisk.
When the sauce is creamy and smooth, combine with the cooked fettucine.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Combine crumbs, butter and sugar.
Press crumb mixture into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 8 minutes at 350°.
Cool. Mix Dream Whip as directed.
Combine 10x sugar and cream cheese. Blend with Dream Whip.
Spread creamed mixture over crumbs.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving. Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: *May substitute 1/2 cup Sweet 'N Low for sugar.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Boil spaghetti as directed on package. Mix browned ground beef and sauce together. Combine spaghetti and sauce mixture together in large casserole dish, top with mozzarella cheese and bake until cheese is melted.

title: 4-stack
directions: Combine the ingredients and mix well.
Pat into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add flour and soda.
Pour into greased pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Now sprinkle top with brown sugar and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
While cake is baking, in a saucepan, combine margarine, evaporated milk and white sugar. Boil 2 minutes and add coconut.
Pour over cake while they are both still hot.

title: chess brownies
directions: In bowl, mix cake mix, margarine and egg together with hands until moist.
Place in ungreased long cake pan.
Spread and mash until pan is covered.

title: golden chiffon cake
directions: Combine cake flour, sugar, baking powder and salt and mix in bowl, then add salad oil, egg yolks, cold water, vanilla and lemon or orange rind.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar very stiff; do not underbeat.
Fold into other mixture.
Pour immediately into ungreased tube pan (10 x 4-inch).
Bake 60 to 65 minutes in 350° oven until golden brown.
Let stand for 1 hour, then remove.

title: black beauty cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and cocoa.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with sour milk (add 1 teaspoon vinegar to sweet milk).
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° in greased 8-inch square pan for 35 minutes.

title: small pecan pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, margarine and flour. Chill before putting in small muffin pan.
Mix all other ingredients for filling and put into muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into crusts. Put extra Cool Whip around top outside edge.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Dribble chocolate syrup over top.
Place in freezer. Remove about 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Cream together first 2 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Fill muffin cups half full.
(Grease pan if not using paper cups.)
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes (test at 25 minutes).

title: party pecans (or walnuts)
directions: Beat egg white until frothy with 1 tablespoon water.
Melt butter in pot.
Add sugar, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Put nuts into egg white and coat well, then put them into sugar mixture. Cover well.
Place in pan with butter and bake at 250° until done.

title: ham 'n mandarin salad
directions: Combine ham, celery, onions, walnuts and orange segments in a bowl. Cover and chill.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, then flour.
Separate into 2 equal amounts and add red food coloring to 1/2 of dough.
Take 1/2 teaspoon amount of dough from each and roll into balls.
Then roll out each to make a long narrow rope of each, and then twist them together and shape into candy cane shapes.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 325° for about 15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: hawaiian beets
directions: Mix sugar, salt, cornstarch and cloves.
Add vinegar.
Pour over pineapple.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add beets and margarine.
Cook until thick.
Cool. Refrigerate overnight.
Heat before serving.
Great with chicken.

title: limeade pie
directions: Mix and pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.

title: colossal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat butter and sugars. Blend in eggs and vanilla. Add peanut butter and soda; mix well. Stir in oats and chips; mix well. Batter will be thick. Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets. Flatten with back of spoon. Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet. Cool completely on wire rack. Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: raisin filled cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together and add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Roll out dough, cutting to desired size.
Place on cookie sheet and put a spoonful of filling on top.
Cover with another cookie; seal around edges.
Bake in 350° oven until slightly brown.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak the 1/2 pound of kidney beans overnight in cold water. Drain.
Add 1/2 pound chopped, smoked ham chunks, celery, onions, green pepper, parsley, bay leaves and garlic.
Cover beans with water.
Simmer 2 hours with lid off.
Then add 1/2 stick margarine. Add black pepper to taste, 1 tablespoon Worcestershire and 1 teaspoon Tabasco and cook for an additional hour.
Remove bay leaves and serve over rice.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Combine sugar, potatoes and butter; mix until smooth.
Add eggs and milk; mix well.
Mix together the flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Mix into batter until well blended. Fold in nuts and raisins.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: homemade chili sauce
directions: Mix together in a 3-quart pan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours or until thick and reduce heat again.
Stir occasionally.
Can be stored in refrigerator for 1 month or frozen in small quantities.
Makes 3 cups.

title: fresh tomato salad
directions: Arrange slices of tomatoes, onions, sweet basil leaf and Mozzarella in an alternating pattern on platter.
Drizzle with olive oil and salt and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add meat; cook until the red is out.
Add broth, 4 cups water and seasonings; cover and simmer 1 hour. Add beans, crushed tomatoes, carrots, potatoes, wine and 2 1/4 cups water. Simmer until vegetables are done (about 20 minutes).
Stir in spinach and macaroni.
Cook 15 minutes.
Watch the macaroni so that it doesn't overcook. Feeds approximately 10.

title: kings bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over baked mixture.
Spread on 1 package of chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: schuler's cheese spread
directions: Heat Velveeta and margarine over low.
Stir together when melted.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Store in plastic tubs or crock jars.
Cool.
Great with Ritz crackers.

title: ron's favorite pork chops
directions: Put pork chops in a pan, single layer.
Open a can of pineapple, either chunks or rings.
Put a piece of pineapple on each pork chop.
Pour pineapple juice into measuring cup and add about half as much soy sauce.
Stir a bit and pour over chops. Bake uncovered about 1 1/2 hours at 375°.
They will brown.
If you throw some baking potatoes and squash into the oven at the same time, you've got your whole dinner.
Don't forget to invite Ron over.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding soda last.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° according to directions on the cake box.

title: fat-free gravy
directions: *To make fat-free meat drippings, refrigerate juices from cooked meats.
Skim the fat off the top of juices and discard. Use the fat-free juices for gravy or seasoning vegetables.

title: carrot ring with peas
directions: Blend eggs, milk and salt.
Stir in carrots and onion.
Pour into 5 cup ring mold.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Unmold; fill with peas and top with butter.
May garnish with parsley.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Bring applesauce to a boil.
Add the frozen strawberries. Stir in jello.
Mix well and refrigerate to set.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Parcook zucchini and onions until they start to soften.
Melt butter and combine with bread crumbs.
Spread 1/2 of bread crumbs on the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown ground round and onions. Put bouillon cube in
hot water; dissolve. Pour into ground round and onions. Put rest of ingredients in with ground round and simmer.

title: jiffy chocolate express cake or lazy woman's chocolate cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Make a well.
Add the rest of the ingredients and stir until smooth (just with a spoon).
Do not overmix.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not overbake. Very simple and hardly ever a failure.

title: finnish chicken rice soup
directions: Boil chicken, celery and onions until chicken is tender. Remove and cut from the bone.
Return chicken to the pot.
Add the cooked rice, allspice and milk.
Heat only; do not boil.
Adding chicken giblets are optional.

title: crumb chicken
directions: Wash chicken thoroughly.
Dip in melted margarine, then in bread crumbs.
Salt, pepper and onion salt.
Sprinkle paprika over top.
Bake in tightly covered (aluminum foil) pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking an additional 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple butter
directions: Mix well.
Bake in oven 3 hours or cook on top of stove.

title: cherry squares
directions: Mix and drop teaspoon of cherry filling on cake batter to make squares.
(Try other fillings.)
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: adobo chicken
directions: Skin chicken; put in mixture.
Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour, turning chicken every 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with rice.
(Use 3 to 4 good size pieces of chicken.)

title: brown rice, chicken and vegetable casserole
directions: Place chicken pieces in microwavable baking dish and sprinkle with garlic salt and pepper.
Microwave on High for 15 minutes (or until done).
Set aside to cool.

title: hot spinach dip
directions: Mix together and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: tender round stuffed roast
directions: Make stuffing mix as directed on box and set aside.
Spread steak out on wax paper.
Sprinkle fairly heavily with garlic salt on both sides.
Spread stuffing mixture all over the steak.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks.
Place in long dish or pan.
Mix soup with 1/2 can of water and pour over rolled roast.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for one hour, basting about halfway through the hour.
Run under broiler to brown if you like, slice and serve. Serves 6 to 8.

title: tuna mousse
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Dissolve over boiling water. Stir in mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients except cream. Chill and fold in whipped cream.
Pour into greased mold and chill until firm.
Good with melon balls for lunch or as an appetizer.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken on bottom of casserole dish.
Cover with mixture.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in water; let set 5 minutes.
Add buttermilk.
Add yeast and buttermilk to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Turn out on slightly floured board; roll or pat to desired thickness and cut into biscuits.
Dip tops in melted margarine and place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.

title: ham rollups
directions: Mix cream cheese and horseradish sauce until creamy.
Spread on ham slices and roll up.
Refrigerate at least one hour.
Cut into 1-2-inch pieces and serve.

title: double crunchers
directions: Sift flour with soda and salt; set aside.
Add both sugars gradually to shortening, creaming well.
Blend in egg and vanilla. Mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in cornflakes, oats and coconut.
Shape by teaspoon into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of a glass dipped in flour.
When cookies are cool, put two cookies together with a good fudge frosting.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into pieces for serving.
Mix flour, salt and pepper. Pound into meat.
Melt fat, add meat and brown well.
Put into greased baking dish; sprinkle mustard and onion on top of meat. Add tomato juice.
Cover and bake in preheated oven at 375° or cook on top of range for approximately one hour.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Brown noodles in butter.
Bring broth to boil in ovenproof pan.
Add rice, salt and browned noodles.
Cover and cook in 400° oven for 45 minutes.
Can be doubled.

title: surprise biscuits
directions: Sift and measure flour.
Cut butter in flour with pastry blender.
Mix in sour cream.
Mix well and drop from tablespoon into greased muffin pans.
Bake in 400 degree oven 10-12 minutes. Yields 48 small biscuits.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and set aside.
Combine eggs, sugar and oil; stir in pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients and mix well. Pour into greased log pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: over-the-rainbow cloud
directions: Spray whipped cream on one side of chocolate wafer.
Spray one side of another wafer and put it on top of first wafer.
Continue this until you have a stack of 5 wafers and whipped cream.
Lay stack of wafers on their side on tray.
Continue making stacks of wafers until tray is filled.
Refrigerate 4 hours so cookies will soften.
When ready to serve, spread remaining whipped cream over cookies to cover entire stack.
Add sprinkles.
Cut stacks diagonally so each piece is striped.
Serves 5 to 8.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Chill dough 1 hour.
Bake at 375°.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
While hot, mix spaghetti with butter, Parmesan cheese and 1 egg.
Butter a 10-inch pie plate with 2 inch rim.
Spread spaghetti over bottom and up sides of pan with back of spoon to form a crust.
Cook sausage and ground beef; add onion and green pepper during last 5 minutes of cooking time.
Drain grease off.
Cut tomatoes in small pieces.
Add tomatoes and their liquid, tomato paste, sugar, oregano, garlic salt to meat mixture.
Cook until hot.
Spread Ricotta cheese over bottom of crust.
Spoon meat mixture on top of cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese or Parmesan cheese in center of pie.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Cut into wedges.

title: quick taco salad(servings:  4 to 6. preparation time:  45 minutes.)
directions: Brown hamburg and drain.
Add olives and taco seasoning mix. Make according to package directions. On plate, place lettuce and tomato and salad dressing. Top with meat mixture, cheese, salsa and crushed chips.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except whipping cream, and mix on slow speed until creamy. Add whipping cream and beat on high speed until mixture has stiffened. Produces 2 cups.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Add water and salad dressing.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: watergate chicken
directions: Lightly salt chicken.
Wrap 1 slice dried beef and 1 slice bacon around each half breast. Place in baking dish. Cook 15 minutes at 400°. Pour off drippings, reserving 1 tablespoon.

title: lemon cheese pie
directions: Combine flour and sugar in large bowl.
Add beaten eggs and oleo.
Beat until blended.
Stir in lemon juice, buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 325°
for 45 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Add all other ingredients (undrained) and cook on medium heat until potatoes are done.

title: upside-down meat loaf
directions: Grease a meat loaf pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar on bottom and pour catsup over it.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Shape into a loaf and put on top of catsup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Spoon excess fat off halfway through cooking and again when done.
Turn upside down on platter to serve.

title: pudding pie cake
directions: Prepare cake according to box.
Bake in an oblong pan.
Mix pudding, cream cheese, milk, vanilla flavorings and sugar until smooth.
Spread on top of cool cake.
Spread pineapple on pudding mixture.
Spread pie filling on top of pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pie filling.
Top with nuts.

title: beth manness' frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Fold in cherries and Cool Whip. Pour into mold and freeze.
Good anytime of year.

title: homemade salad dressing
directions: Mix in blender for about 1 1/2 minutes.

title: pineapple bread(no sugar)
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Combine egg, oil and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients along with pineapple, stirring just until ingredients are moistened.
Fold in raisins.
Spread evenly in greased pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
For easier slicing, store overnight in refrigerator before serving. Recipes makes 34 (1/4-inch) slices.
Calories per 1/4 slice:

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Dredge chicken in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown chicken in oil.
Remove chicken; brown onion in oil.
Put chicken back in oil.
Add about 1 1/2-quarts of water.
Let cook until chicken is tender, stirring to keep from sticking.
Should be thick gravy. Ten minutes before serving, add green onion tops.

title: chicken and mushrooms in beer
directions: Place chicken in crock-pot; add all ingredients to pot.
Cook on low for 6 to 7 hours.

title: rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
If using instant rice, bake for 1/2 hour.

title: oven baked rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a buttered baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour, stirring once.

title: lemon yogurt bread
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients (stir in nuts).
Set aside.
Beat eggs in large bowl; add oil and sugar and cream well.
Add yogurt and extract.
Mix all ingredients by folding only until mixed. Spoon into 2 well-greased loaf pans or 1 large well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: puppy chow
directions: Microwave peanut butter, butterscotch chips, chocolate chips and margarine stirring until smooth.
Mix with cereal in large bowl.
Shake with confectioners sugar in paper bag.
Serve in small dog food bowls.
Makes a great conversation snack at parties.

title: neiman-marcus brownies
directions: Mix cake mix with 1 stick melted butter and 1 egg.
Past into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Go up sides of pan.
Mix powdered sugar with 2 eggs, 1 stick melted butter and cream cheese and beat.
Pour over first layer.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake in oven at 300° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool until firm.

title: heath candy
directions: Chop nuts; mix all ingredients except chocolate bars in a large pan.
Boil gently until a candy thermometer shows "hard crack" stage.
Pour mixture onto a greased cookie sheet. Immediately lay chocolate bars on the top.
When they are melted, spread over all with a spatula.
When cool, break up candy.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Mix ingredients (except onion rings) together; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add onion rings and brown.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon.
Make 4 patties approximately 1-inch thick.
Wrap slice of bacon around each. Fasten bacon with toothpick.
Broil 7 to 10 minutes on each side.

title: easy peach crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Pour peaches into lightly buttered 2-quart baking dish. Combine instant oatmeal, flour and nuts into bowl. Stir in butter. Sprinkle over peaches. Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown. Serve over ice cream, if desired.

title: chicken-rice delight
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Combine with remaining ingredients except potato chips.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Sprinkle with potato chips and bake at 350° for about 1 hour, or until hot and bubbly.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix until smooth 1 cup sugar, shortening, eggs, milk and lemon extract; add flour, baking powder, salt and lemon rind. Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown and wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Chill thoroughly.
Roll out on floured wax paper.
Roll out thick.
Bake until barely done.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Mix flour, salt, soda and spices together.
Add nuts and raisins with flour mixture.
Mix egg with persimmon.
Alternate egg mixture with flour mixture as you beat into creamed sugar and shortening.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 375°.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook onions and pepper in shortening until tender.
Add meat and cook until browned.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well. Put into casserole dish with a lid.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together the chocolate chips, oleo and peanut butter. Pour over Corn Chex and stir.
Put 2 1/2 cups powdered sugar in a paper sack and shake until all the cereal is coated.
Finished. Great snack!

title: parsnips casserole
directions: Cook parsnips in a deep pan with milk and fryings.
Add salt, pepper and sugar.
Cook until tender; mash like potatoes, put in a greased casserole dish.
Add a few dots of butter or margarine; sprinkle with a little sugar.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: spaghetti confetti
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and rinse well.
Add to remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: berry good topping
directions: Peel and halve pears. Soak pears in a gallon of water with 1 1/2 tbsp salt. Soak overnight in refrigerator. Drain water off pears. make a syrup of 1 part water and 2 parts sugar or 1 part water and 1 part sugar; which ever you prefer. Cook pears in syrup, bring to a boil for 4-8 minutes. Pour into fruit jars and seal.

title: frankfurters in a loaf
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease loaf pan.
Split frankfurters lengthwise, not cutting completely through.
Fill with cheese or relish.
Beat remaining ingredients with fork for 30 seconds. Spread in pan. Arrange frankfurters crosswise on dough, curving slightly to fit pan and pressing slightly into dough.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: pecan cream cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Cream together with one egg, 4 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
In another bowl, beat together corn syrup, remaining 1 teaspoon vanilla, 3 eggs and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Pour cheese mixture into pie shell. Sprinkle chopped pecans over cheese mixture.
Pour second mixture over pecans.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: gummi bears
directions: Mix in saucepan until the mixture resembles play dough. Place pan over low heat and stir until melted.
When completely melted, pour into plastic candy molds, and place in the freezer for 5 minutes.

title: california quiche
directions: Start with crust.
Repeat layers of Monterey Jack, Cheddar, chilies and olives.
Combine milk, flour and eggs and pour over layers.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Pour tomato sauce over top.
Sprinkle a little cheese on top.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased baking dish. (Double recipe for a larger pan.) For a zestier taste, jalapeno peppers can be added. Bake for 30 to 45 minutes in a 350° to 400° oven.

title: bread sticks(like pizza parlors)
directions: Melt oleo in oven in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix dry ingredients. Stir just enough milk in until dough forms (about 30 strokes). Turn dough onto floured surface.
Roll dough in flour to coat. Knead lightly, about 10 times.
Roll into 8-inch square.
With floured knife, cut dough in half, then cut each half into 9 (4-inch) strips.
Dip each strip into melted oleo, coating each side.
Arrange strips close together in pan.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown at 425°.

title: gram's vegetable soup
directions: Add all ingredients and cook until it boils, then simmer. Cabbage should be crisp.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
If mixture is too dry, add some water.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 1 large or 2 small loaves.

title: chocolate cream cheese surprise
directions: Mix as for pie crust and pat into baking dish. Bake in a 350° oven until golden.

title: seafood linguine
directions: Cook pasta.
Saute garlic and oregano in butter, stirring frequently for 1 minute.
Add tomato; cook 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until cheese is melted.
Place hot, cooked pasta on serving plate.
Top with sauce.

title: delicious homemade bread from scotland
directions: Mix flours, salt and margarine or lard in warm bowl.
Then mix last 3 ingredients in container.
Leave to rise.
Mix flour with yeast.
Knead for 10 minutes.
Leave to rise double in size. Knead lightly.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Fry on griddle.
Brown on both sides.

title: sugar and spice pecans(don't buy them at the mall - make your own!)
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. Set aside. Beat egg whites (at room temperature) and water until foamy. Gradually add the sugar mixture, one tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks form. Fold in pecan halves. Pour pecans on well-greased 15 x 10 x 1 jelly roll pan. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes. Cool and store in airtight container.

title: cheesy green beans
directions: Cook and stir mushrooms and onion on medium-high heat in oil for 10 minutes; drain.
Microwave beans as directed on package; drain well.
Add mushrooms and onion to hot green beans.
Mix lightly.
Spoon into 2-quart serving dish.
Microwave Cheez Whiz Light as directed on label.
Pour over green bean mixture.
Makes 10 servings.

title: picante sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage in medium pot on medium heat; drain.
Add cream cheese; stir until blended.
Add picante sauce; stir until blender.
Pour into medium size bowl; add sour cream.

title: crab quiche
directions: Fit pie crust into a 10 or 11-inch quiche or pie pan.
Prick bottom of shell and chill while preparing quiche filling.

title: low-fat biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spray muffin tin with Pam (we use muffin baking papers).
Cook 15 to 18 minutes at 450° or until brown.
Makes 12 biscuits.
Yields 37 calories each.

title: bible scripture cake
directions: This recipe takes a bit of Bible research.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together Judges 5:25 and Jeremiah 17:11.
Separate eggs.
Add yolks, along with 1 Samuel 14:25 to creamed mixture. Reserve egg whites; sift dry ingredients.
Dice fruit; dust lightly with flour.
Mix in batter thoroughly, then fold in egg whites.
Pour into greased Jeremiah 52:19 and put into Leviticus 26:26 for 1 3/4 hours.
Add a creamy nut frosting.

title: homemade maple syrup
directions: Heat all ingredients until boiling.
Terrific on hot cakes and waffles.
Keeps good in refrigerator.

title: chocolate chip meringue cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy; add salt and cream of tartar. Beat until stiff enough to hold peaks, but not dry.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition; fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon on ungreased heavy paper.
Bake for 25 minutes at 300°.
Remove from paper while warm.

title: honey apricot bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Mix egg, milk, honey and margarine.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir just until moistened.
Stir in cereal and apricots.
Pour into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan which has been sprayed with no stick cooking spray.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Warm (not hot), on the stove or in the microwave:
applesauce, white sugar, soda, crisco, and brown sugar.
Sift flour, allspice, cinnamon, and cloves.
Add to applesauce mixture with eggs, raisins, vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in tube pan.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all in one bowl.
Beat 4 to 6 minutes with mixer.
Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350°.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Combine cake mix, undrained fruit, 1 cup of coconut and eggs; blend.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Bring butter, sugar and milk to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Stir in remaining coconut; spoon over warm cake.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: imperial cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream Imperial margarine ("Imperial" is a must) and sugar until margarine turns light and fluffy, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir in vinegar and soda.
Add flour.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
If desired, a nut or sprinkles can be added.
Bake 15 minutes or until lightly browned on bottom.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Soften cheese and blend in mayonnaise and sugar.
Add cranberry sauce and drained pineapple.
Stir in nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into mold (or 20 cupcake papers).
Cover tightly and freeze overnight.
Store in freezer and allow a few minutes to soften before trying to serve.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large plastic bag, shake potatoes until evenly covered.
Empty potatoes into baking pan.
Bake 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice into casserole 1 layer of sweet potatoes at a time.
Sprinkle each layer with brown sugar, spice and butter. Make 2 or 3 layers, depending on size of skillet or casserole. Sprinkle with salt. Cover tightly and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna casserole 2
directions: Combine all ingredients except onions.
Bake at 350° in casserole dish for 20 minutes.
Add onions and broil until browned.
Serves 4.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix and keep in a closed jar.
Refrigerate.
Use 1 to 2 teaspoons per cup of tea.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Blend sugars and shortening and beat in the eggs and vanilla. Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Add flour mixture and pineapple to creamed mixture and blend well.
Drop by tablespoon on buttered cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for about 15 minutes. Do not allow cookies to brown.
They should be moist.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: sweet poppy seed loaf bread
directions: Lightly beat eggs in large bowl; add oil, milk and vanilla and beat well.
Add dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Turn into pans and bake until tested with broomstick.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 35 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat together sugar, margarine and eggs.
Add bananas with water and salt.
Stir in flour, baking soda, baking powder and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Makes 1 large loaf or 2 small loaves.

title: shredded beef sandwiches
directions: This can be be cooked slowly in the oven or in your crock-pot. Place meat in pot and top with onion.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Put 1/2 stick of butter in pan and melt in 450° oven.
Mix flour, salt and milk.
Add eggs and cold water.
Mix together. Add batter to melted, browned butter and cook until brown.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix and beat sugar, oil and eggs.
Combine flour, salt, cinnamon and soda and mix.
Add apples, nuts, coconut, raisins and vanilla.
Pour into pan.
Bake 325° for one hour 20 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken in boiling water.
Drain and rinse; dice chicken. Cook broccoli in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and Stove Top dressing.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serve with rice (optional).
Serves 4.

title: cheese broccoli soup
directions: Bring water to boil in 3 quart pan, add broccoli and onion. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Add cheese and seasoning, stirring until cheese melts.
Stir in milk, half & half, and butter, cook over low heat until thoroughly heated. Combine flour and water, stirring until smooth.
Gradually add to broccoli mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Melt shortening, add brown sugar and stir.
Remove from heat.
Add pumpkin, add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sift powdered sugar over bars.
Yield: 52 (1 1/2 inch square).
Carbohydrate .4 g, protein 1 g, fat 2 g, calories 52.
One serving = 1/2 fruit exchange, 1/2 fat exchange.

title: vidalia onions
directions: Melt butter or margarine in large frying pan.
Saute onions over medium heat until clear.
Reserve 3 tablespoons crumbs for topping.
Place remaining crumbs in bottom of lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Remove onions with slotted spoon.
Add soup and onions in layers.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Melt marshmallows with margarine in a large saucepan over low heat, stirring until completely melted.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Using greased spatula or waxed paper, press mixture evenly into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into square when cool.
Yields 24.

title: can't fail pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut lard into flour until fine and crumbly.
Blend water, vinegar and egg.
Stir.
Pour in flour mixture and stir until well combined.
Roll on floured surface. Makes 1 double and 1 single crust.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: easy chocolate chip icing
directions: In a microwave melt the chocolate chips and butter.
Add the vanilla, milk and confectioners sugar; mix well.
The icing will be soft and pourable.
It will set as it cools.

title: henry's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
This will really wake up your taste buds!

title: rolls
directions: Mix
cup flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Heat milk, water and margarine to 120°.

minutes at medium speed.
Add 1/4 cup flour; beat at

shape into balls.
Bake at 275° until done.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water for 10 minutes or until tender; drain.
Melt butter; stir in syrup and ginger; cook 1 minute. Pour glaze over carrots.
Stir and garnish with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tony's cube steak stacks
directions: Sprinkle the steaks with cracked pepper, using from 1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon, depending on your taste preference.
Preheat broiler. Heat the oil and butter in heavy skillet.
Brown the steaks quickly about 4 minutes per side.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Stir in vegetables, chicken and water chestnuts.
Put into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with cornflake crumbs (combined with butter).
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat
oven to 375°.
Beat together margarine and sugars until light
and	fluffy.
Beat
in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour
and spice;
add
to
margarine mixture.
Stir in oats. Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10
minutes for
chewy
cookie,
to
11 minutes for crisp cookie.	Cool for 1 minute on cookie sheet before removing to wire rack.	Yield: 4 1/2 dozen.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook onions in shortening until onions are yellow; add hamburger and salt.
Cook until mixture falls apart.
Add tomatoes, rice and other seasonings.
Put in casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix boiling water and jello; set aside and let cool.
Mix cake mix and all other ingredients.
Put jello mix into cake mix and other ingredients.

title: charlie brown's party mix
directions: Microwave Directions:
In large microwave-safe bowl, melt margarine on High 1 minute.
Stir in seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Gradually add cereal, nuts and pretzels, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Microwave on High, 5 to 6 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening and add eggs, flavorings and buttermilk.
Sift flour, soda and salt; add and mix well.
Add German chocolate, that has been softened.
Blend together well. Bake in well-greased and floured angel food or Bundt pan about 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Remove cake from pan while hot and place under tight fitting cake cover.
Leave covered until cold.
Ice with German Chocolate Pound Cake Glaze.

title: fried cookies or rosette cookies
directions: You will also need an electric frying pan, rosette iron and tongs for picking up cookies.

title: theresa's cookie recipe from nova scotia
directions: Stir dry ingredients together, add wet ingredients and beat. Make small balls and dip in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Watch carefully and let set on cookie sheet to cook before removing.

title: rice krispie peanut butter bars
directions: Dissolve white sugar and syrup on stove; do not boil. Add the peanut butter. Add this mixture to the Rice Krispies cereal.
Mix and spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt the chocolate chips and spread over top.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: peanut patties
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in a large pan and bring to a boil. Boil on low heat (mixture barely boiling) for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add the butter, vanilla and food coloring.
Beat until stiff and spoon on buttered cookie sheet to cool.

title: grandma's turkey dressing
directions: When you buy the duck, have the butcher halve the duck; split it in half right up the middle and figure 1/2 duck per person. Duck needs to be cooked on a rack and the fat drained from time to time lest the meat be and taste greasy.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer cheese and bacon in well-buttered 8 x 12-inch ovenproof dish or pan.
Mix together eggs and milk and pour over.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter and cheese in medium saucepan on medium-low.
Cook rice according to instructions.
In large casserole dish, add broccoli, celery, onion, soup and cheese mixture.
Add rice and stir until mixed.
Bake in oven for 1 hour. Top with Cheddar cheese (optional).

title: corn puff casserole
directions: In bowl, combine eggs, milk, onion, eggs and pepper.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into ungreased casserole.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes in 350° oven or until a table knife inserted 1-inch in center comes out clean.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Set up ingredients in line up order. Spread sauce on English muffins. Add pepperoni slices and cheese. Place in toaster oven until done.

title: festive roasted pepper dip
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended; refrigerate.
Serve with vegetable dippers or corn chips.
Makes 3 cups.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; add sugar and beat until smooth. Add egg yolks and beat until smooth.
Combine flour and soda; add to creamed mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla. Add nuts and coconut.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350° or until tests done.

title: julie's brownie balls
directions: Melt in microwave on High, the first three items for 1 1/2 minutes. Stir in the flour and nuts.
Let dough set for 5 to 10 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon and bake for 7 minutes.

title: maryland lady crab cakes
directions: Remove all cartilage from crabmeat.
In a bowl, mix breadcrumbs, eggs, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Add crabmeat and mix gently but thoroughly.
If mixture is too dry, add a little more mayonnaise.
Shape into 6 cakes.

title: reuben spread
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve with cocktail rye bread.

title: jill's lemon squares
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with pastry blender and make a crust. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix egg mixture and pour over crust.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Sift confectioners sugar over while hot; cut into squares.

title: pot roast with mushroom gravy
directions: This works on any size roast. Preheat oven to 375°. Have roast standing at room temperature for 45 minutes. At 3:00 p.m., place roast in oven and cook for 1 hour. Turn oven off. KEEP DOOR CLOSED. Forty-five minutes before serving, turn oven on to 300°. At the end of this time, remove roast; cover with foil for 10 minutes before slicing. Roast will be juicy and medium-rare. Perfect every time.

title: salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in quart bottle.
Mix well.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In baking dish, melt butter.
Add salt, garlic and parsley.
Add shrimp and bake uncovered for 5 minutes.
Turn shrimp over.
Sprinkle with lemon and parsley. Bake for 10 minutes and serve.

title: sweet potatoes casserole
directions: Mix well and put topping on and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen liquor drink
directions: Boil or microwave the water.
Dip tea bag in the boiled water for a few minutes.
Put in large container that can be put in the freezer.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place in freezer.
Let set overnight.
Scoop out and place in glasses.
Pour 7-Up over; stir with spoon.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon
and onions until slightly brown.
Add water, salt, pepper
and Tabasco.
Bring to a boil.
Add tomatoes and simmer 30	minutes.
Add
vegetables
and	clams.	Simmer	30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Add all other ingredients.
Stir until mixed.
Do not beat. Pour into a well-greased floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: strawberry mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; cool.
Add drained pineapple and strawberries; cool and add bananas.
Pour half of mixture in mold; let set.
Top with sour cream, then spoon on rest of Jell-O mixture and refrigerate.

title: cheese broccoli soup
directions: Steam broccoli and onion until tender.
Remove from heat and chop.
Place half and half, water and bouillon cube in top of double boiler.
Add cheese, salt and pepper; heat until all cheese melts.
Add broccoli.
Mix together cornstarch and water in small bowl.
Stir into the cheese mixture in the double boiler and heat over simmering water until the soup thickens.

title: fresh tomato sauce with mushrooms
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan.
Add mushrooms, onions, garlic, basil, salt, pepper and oregano.
Saute until onions are transparent.
Stir in tomatoes.
Reduce heat and cook for 1 hour or until mixture begins to thicken.
Serve over your choice of pasta.
Garnish with grated Romano cheese.
Makes 3 to 3 1/2 cups.

title: tomato beef or turkey stew
directions: Cook meat with onion until brown (no longer pink).
Stir and separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, water, beans, carrots and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat to simmering.
Cook 10 minutes or longer until hot.
Makes 6 cups.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat well.
Pour into the pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: elegant chicken
directions: Cut chicken in strips.
In large bowl, combine chicken, salt and pepper.
Cover and let set overnight, refrigerated.

title: aunt charm's punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice, juice of 2 limes or frozen lime juice, lemons, oranges and sugar.
Let set for 12 hours.
Add ginger ale and carbonated water.

title: cool and creamy coconut cake
directions: This cake is best prepared a day or two ahead so all the liquid gets absorbed.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a pot. Bring to a boil; cover and simmer 5 minutes. Remove potatoes and reserve broth. Layer half of potatoes and Swiss cheese in greased casserole. Repeat layers. Pour reserved broth over top and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 55 minutes. Remove cover and bake 5 minutes longer, until potatoes are tender and cheese golden brown.

title: baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half.
Scoop out potatoes and mash.
Add butter, seasoning, onion and egg yolks.
Add milk and mash again. Beat egg whites.
When stiff, fold whites and cheese into mashed potatoes.
Fill shells and bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking oil. Dump into pan the cake mix, water, pineapple, oranges, eggs and 3/4 cup coconut. Mixture will be lumpy and runny after stirring in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Remove from oven and punch holes in top while hot.
Pour cream of coconut over hot cake.
Let cake cool completely.
Mix together remaining 3/4 cup coconut and Cool Whip and spread over top of cooled cake. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Mix sugar and butter well; add vanilla.
Beat eggs well.
Add raisins and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: texas grits
directions: Bring water to boil.
Do not add salt to water.
Add grits and cook until done.
Beat eggs and add remaining ingredients to hot grits.
Stir well until cheese and margarine are melted.
Put in large baking dish and bake 1 hour at 250.

title: exquistie pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° until brown.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all but cornbread, then mix the cornbread mix and stir. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: fresh green apple nut cake
directions: Sift
flour,
baking
powder,
baking
soda,
salt
and cinnamon in
a large bowl.	Add chopped apples, oil and vanilla; beat
for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Beat eggs; gradually add sugar.
Fold egg mixture into apple mixture.
Blend well. Stir in nuts.
Bake
in a tube pan at 350° for 70 minutes, or until well done.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add lemon juice; cool to room temperature.
Soften sherbet.
Fold into jello mixture.
Add oranges and pour into dish or mold.
Refrigerate.

title: chewy bread
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Put mixture in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at
for
to 45 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Cool before cutting.

title: chocolate buttermilk cake
directions: Cream together oil, sugar and eggs.
Add cocoa, salt, flour and buttermilk.
Add 1 teaspoon soda to 1 cup boiling water last. Bake in sheet pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve orange juice with boiling water. Add mandarin oranges, then pineapple. Return to heat and add marshmallows and let dissolve. After this thickens, add sour cream and mayonnaise. Fold in and chill.

title: kool-aid pie
directions: Whip the canned milk until fluffy; add one cup of sugar.
Beat on high until well mixed.
Add Kool-Aid and beat until it stands in a peak.
Pour in prepared crust.
Should stand very high. Serves 6.

title: minnesota hot dish
directions: Mix and put in bottom of casserole.
Slice 4 cups of raw potatoes and one large onion.
Put potatoes on top of mixture, then top with sliced onion.
Pour milk to almost cover mixture. Bake at 350° for one hour or until potatoes are soft.

title: chicken with rice(very easy, very good)
directions: Use a large, covered pan.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven, covered, for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and slice sweet potatoes. Put in a skillet that has been sprayed with cooking oil. Dot butter all over potatoes. Cover and let cook on medium heat. Turn potatoes occasionally. When almost done, add sugar. Sprinkle over top. Keep lid on and reduce heat to low. Cook until done and sugar dissolves.

title: pizza
directions: Make the crust.
Roll it out and put it in the oven.

title: oil pastry
directions: Resift the flour into a mixing bowl.
Combine oil and milk without stirring.
Add all at once to flour.
Mix with a fork until well blended.
Form into a ball and place on a sheet of wax paper.
Place another piece of wax paper on top of the pastry and roll out into a circle large enough to fit the top of the 8-inch pie dish and hang over the edge by half an inch.

title: chocolate covered nuts
directions: In top of double boiler, melt chocolate.
Gradually stir in milk.
Remove chocolate mixture from hot water and cool 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in nuts, mixing so they are well covered.
Drop by teaspoonful on lightly buttered baking sheet.
If using whole nuts or perfect halves, separate by piece.
Wrap in waxed paper, if desired.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: aunt ethel's tea cake recipe(a large batch)
directions: In a large bowl or pan, put flour in.
Add all sugar.
Mix it well.
Beat eggs well.
Add milk, flavoring, oil and Crisco.
Melt butter ahead and let cool enough so as not to cook eggs, then put all these ingredients in flour and sugar.
Mix well.
When you have it all mixed well, you can keep adding or sprinkle a little flour on top of dough just enough so you can handle it.
Pinch it off in small biscuits.
Roll it as a biscuit and place on greased pan.
A shiny pan will bake them better than a dark one.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake until done.
Check them in about 20 to 25 minutes.
Some ovens bake faster than others.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Crumble ground beef into a 2-quart glass casserole; add onion and garlic.
Microwave, uncovered, on Full power, for 5 to 6 minutes or until meat is set, stirring once.
Drain.
Stir remaining ingredients, except cheeses into meat mixture. Microwave, covered, for 15 to 17 minutes or until noodles are tender, on Full power, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Microwave, uncovered, for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until cheeses are melted on Full power.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: eugene's favorite chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Sift all ingredients together. add 2 cups buttermilk and beat well.
Add 1/2 cup melted shortening, beat again.
Add 1 tsp. pure vanilla, beat again. Bake in 13 x 9 inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes or until done when tested with toothpick.

title: lemon glazed zucchini muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease well or paper-line 12 muffin cups.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and lemon peel.
Stir in nuts and raisins.

title: no-cook chocolate cream cheese fudge
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix cocoa with sugar until smooth. Cream in cheese, add vanilla, salt and nuts if desired.
Spread in buttered dish and cool in refrigerator.

title: cinnamon pull aparts
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Place nuts in bottom.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Roll in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Arrange in pan.
Melt margarine and brown sugar.
Pour over sugared biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Place upside down on plate.
Enjoy! Serves 8 to 10.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix all together and put in a well greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in punch bowl.

title: flour sopaipillas
directions: Shape dough into 2 parts.
Let stand 1 hour or more.
Roll out very thin.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch squares.
Drop into very hot grease.

title: greek corn bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: baked sausage beans
directions: Cook sausage; drain and crumble.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, mix butter and peanut butter on high for 30 seconds.
Add 1/2 cup flour, sugar, brown sugar, egg, baking soda, baking powder and vanilla.
Beat until well mixed.
Then beat in remaining flour.

title: swiss green beans
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter and blend in flour, pepper, Accent (if used) and a little salt if desired.
Remove from heat; add sour cream and mustard, stirring constantly.
Heat but do not boil.
Add beans, cheese and onions.
Turn into a greased casserole.
Top with toasted bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: nut pound cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add nuts last.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: angel cake surprise
directions: Slice off top one-third of cake; set aside.
Using a sharp knife, hollow out center of remaining cake, leaving 1-inch shell; reserve cake pieces for other uses.
Place cake shell on serving plate and set aside.

title: pear and walnut salad
directions: Drain pears, save 1 cup pear juice; set pears aside.
In 2-cup measure, combine cornstarch, brown sugar, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Blend in pear juice.
Microwave on High 2 to 5 minutes, until thick, stirring 1 or 2 times.
Set aside.
Put pears in 9-inch pie plate.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes, until hot.
Line salad plates with lettuce leaves, put pears on lettuce, top with walnuts.
Put 2 to 3 tablespoons juice on top.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.

Fold in thawed strawberries with juice, drained pineapple, bananas and nuts. Pour 1/2 mixture into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan and chill until firm. Spread top with sour cream and gently spoon on rest of mixture. Chill until firm.

title: salmon-brown rice casserole
directions: In a large bowl, mix together all ingredients except the paprika. When well blended, place in 1-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Serve hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Saute carrot, scallion, celery and parsley in 2 tablespoons of butter.
Peel and dice potatoes and place in 4 to 6-quart pot with enough water to cover.
Stir in saute mixture and soup base. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, until potatoes are done.

title: abbott family chow-chow
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large kettle.
Bring to a boil; boil for 5 minutes.
Pack in sterilized jars.
Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Yields 18 to 20 pints.

title: chicken coq au vin(chicken in wine sauce)
directions: Dip chicken in flour and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Brown the chicken.
Add all other ingredients in saucepan to chicken and simmer, covered, 45 to 50 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add zucchini, oil, sugars, and vanilla.
Mix lightly, but well.
Add salt, soda, and baking powder.
(Note:
If using self-rising flour, eliminate salt, soda, and baking powder.) Add cinnamon, flour, and chopped nuts.
Mix everything together well.
Pour into a well-greased loaf pan (9 X 5 1/2 X 3 inches). Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, or until done in center.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour nuts and coconut in pan; set aside.
Prepare cake mix and pour over pecans.
In separate bowl, cream together cream cheese, butter, sugar and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons over batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: 24-hour slaw(keeps 3 weeks in refrigerator.)
directions: Boil vinegar, sugar, mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper until sugar dissolves.
Add oil.
Put cabbage, onion and green pepper in a large bowl.
Pour liquid mixture over dry vegetables. Do not stir.
Store in refrigerator at least 24 hours before serving.
Stir gently before serving.

title: chilled vegetable salad
directions: Bring first three ingredients to a boil in a small sauce pan over medium heat; cook, stirring often, 5 minutes or until sugar dissolves. Remove dressing from heat and cool
for 30 minutes. Stir together chopped bell pepper and next 8 ingredients in a large bowl; gently stir in dressing. Cover and chill salad for 8 hours. Serve with a slotted spoon.

title: jeannie's ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: rouladen(beef rolls)
directions: Pound steak to about 1/4 to 3/8-inch thick.
Salt and pepper steak; spread each piece with mustard.
Mix bacon and onions together; spread on beef slices.
Roll slices tightly.
Tie with string, or fasten with toothpicks.
Brown in oil.
Add water. Finish cooking in a 350° oven for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Take rolls out.
Mix cornstarch with a little water.
Add to drippings in pan.
Cook to thicken.
To serve, pour gravy over rolls.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken in small amount of water until tender.
Remove chicken and set aside 1 cup of broth.
Cut chicken into chunks and put in a greased baking dish (13 x 9-inch).
Cover chicken with cooked, drained broccoli.

title: appetizer spread
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and store in refrigerator. This makes an excellent appetizer with crackers or sandwich spread.

title: mom's vegetable soup
directions: Sear the meat in the kettle.
Add the remaining ingredients except the barley.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or longer.
