Add the barley and cook 45 minutes longer. Serve with fresh bread or biscuits and a light fruited Jell-O for dessert.

title: date bread
directions: Sift and mix all dry ingredients. Add liquid, syrup and slightly beaten egg. Add dates. Turn into pans. Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: johnny marzetti(great for a teenage crowd.)
directions: Saute meat and onion in bacon fat.
Add rest of ingredients, reserving 1/2 of cheese.
Cook noodles and add to meat mixture. Cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Add remaining cheese to top before serving.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Whip Dream Whip according to package directions until half whipped (about 2 minutes).
Add sugar and cream cheese.
Beat until creamy.
Pour over cooled crust.
Top with blueberry filling which has been cooled.

title: crock-pot steak soup
directions: Put all ingredients except butter and flour in crock-pot. Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours.
One hour before serving, turn to high.
Mix 1/2 cup melted butter and 1/2 cup flour.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into crock-pot and stir until thickened.
Cook on high 1/2 hour longer.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs.
Peel.
Cut in half.
Take out yolks.
Smash with fork.
Add relish, green onion, mustard, salt and pepper to taste. Add salad dressing or mayo to desired consistency.
Mix until well blended.
Spoon mixture into hollowed egg halves.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Refrigerate.

title: k.f.c.  (copy) coleslaw
directions: Combine ingredients and chill 2 hours.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain.
Wash and separate broccoli and cauliflower into bite-sized pieces.
Half the cherry tomatoes.
Mix the Caesar dressing according to package directions.
Mix cooled pasta and vegetables together.
Pour on dressing; toss.

title: milk chocolate bubble ring
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spread shortening around a ring mold.
Put margarine in a saucepan and heat on low until melted.
Separate the biscuits and flatten into a 3-inch circle.
Place a chocolate kiss in the center of a biscuit.
Wrap around chocolate forming a ball.
Pinch edges to seal firmly.
Repeat for each one.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat.
Add vinegar, food coloring and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients; alternate with buttermilk. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sam's chili
directions: Combine all ingredients in heavy, small saucepan over medium heat.
Cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: rice casserole
directions: In large pan, mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: white chip brownies
directions: Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt in a medium bowl. Beat butter and sugar together in large mixing bowl.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups morsels. Pour into greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until wooden pick inserted near center comes out slightly sticky.
Cool in pan on wire rack (brownies will sink in center when cooled).
Melt remaining morsels; drizzle over top of brownies.
Makes 16 brownies.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla; beat well. Add zucchini.
Mix lightly.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
2 small and 1 large loaves or 2 very large loaves.

title: twinkie delight cake
directions: Split Twinkies in half.
Place in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Slice bananas on top of Twinkies.
Add crushed pineapple.
Make instant pudding as directed on box and spread on top of the pineapple. Chill. Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle nuts on top of Cool Whip. Keep in refrigerator.

title: foolproof meringue
directions: The "friendship" idea started
from
the
fact that you must obtain a cup and a half of Starter from a friend.
If you cannot get the Starter, I have heard
that
you
can use a cup and a half of juice from a
can
of peaches.
I have not tried this personally.
I have always
obtained
my
Starter
from a friend and in turn passed a Starter on to my friends.

title: christmas ornaments
directions: With dry ingredients in a bowl, add water a little at a time. Mix it into the powder with your fingers until the dough clings together.
Knead dough for 10 minutes or until consistency is smooth and elastic.
Roll into quarter-inch sheet on wax paper over a cutting board.
Use Christmas cookie cutter or thin tipped knife to cut shapes.
Poke a hole in dough with ice pick or 6 penny nail near top to serve as hanger hole.

title: applesauce salad (molded)
directions: Dissolve candy in the boiling water until all is dissolved. Pour over gelatin; stir until gelatin is all dissolved. Add applesauce and stir. Pour in mold or squares and serve on lettuce leaf. Garnish with green grapes.
Serves 9.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box. When cake is taken from oven, fill full of holes with wooden spoon handle. Immediately pour Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut over cake. Let cake cool and cover with pineapple then spread Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.

title: raspberry chicken with plantains(prep time:  30 minutes)
directions: Prepare charcoal grill or preheat gas grill for medium heat. For sauce, combine raspberries and granulated sugar in a small saucepan. Heat over low heat about 3 minutes or until berries are softened. Press berry mixture through a fine-mesh sieve; discard seeds. Set aside.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream both shortenings, sugar and brown sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat until well mixed.
Add vanilla; beat again. Add 2 1/4 cups flour with 1 teaspoon baking soda; blend into batter.
Add remaining flour and soda; blend well.
Add chocolate chips; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Don't overbake.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a glass quart size casserole bowl, put in green beans and soup.
Mix together.
Layer onion rings on top of the mixture. Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: christmas wreath cookies
directions: Melt margarine in medium saucepan; add marshmallows and food coloring.
Stir until cooled.
Add 3 cups corn flakes.
Place by tablespoonfuls on buttered wax paper.
With buttered fingers, form wreaths.
Sprinkle with red sugar granules.

title: kentucky dish
directions: Brown beef, onion and peppers in 3 tablespoons shortening. Arrange this and rice in layers with corn.
Mix seasonings with tomatoes.
Pour over casserole.
Bake covered 2-quart dish at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: no bake apricot cheese cake
directions: In blender, puree 10 apricot halves with reserved syrup; heat to boiling.
Meanwhile, in large bowl, mix Knox gelatine with sugar.
Add hot liquid and stir until gelatine is completely dissolved, about 5 minutes with electric mixer.
Beat in cream cheese and vanilla until smooth.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with remaining apricot halves (sliced) and whipped cream, if desired.

title: fresh strawberry cake
directions: Mix together cake mix and jello.
Add oil, water and eggs and beat.
Add strawberries.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: "perfect" pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Add vanilla, lemon rind and salt.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients, alternating with sour cream.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool in pan for 30 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to directions; drain well and squeeze to remove excess moisture.
Combine spinach and remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls and place on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes or can be fried in butter on stove.
Can be frozen prior to baking.

title: hawaiian bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add nuts and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to dry ingredients and stir until just moist.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook onions and hamburger; drain.
Add green pepper, chili powder, tomatoes and uncooked rice.
Cook slowly until rice is done.

title: mexican black-eyed peas
directions: Wash peas and put in Dutch oven.
Add stewed tomatoes to peas and cover with water.
Add salt, pepper and chili powder to taste. Cut Polish sausage into quarters and add to mixture.
Cook until peas are tender.
Serve over rice.

title: veg-all salad
directions: Drain Veg-All.
Mix chopped egg, chopped onion, pickle relish and mayonnaise with Veg-All.
Chill and serve.

title: easy no-cook mints
directions: Thoroughly blend margarine, Karo syrup, salt and extract in large bowl.
Add sifted powdered sugar; mix with spoon and hands until blended smooth.
Knead food coloring into mixture.
Shape into small balls; then flatten with tines of fork on wax paper. Let dry a few hours.

title: brown sugar barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes, uncovered.
Remove cloves.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
(Cook until syrupy.)

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar syrup and oleo, add corn starch to sugar before mixing.
Then add eggs and vanilla mix well, now add pecans that have been chopped, pour into two pie shells and bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Cube bread and place in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Beat eggs.
Add milk and beat.
Add mustard and mix. Add cheese and sausage and mix.
Pour into pan over bread cubes. Place in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to bake, bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Grease pan.
Place rhubarb in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add sugar on top, then sprinkle dry jello.
Top with marshmallows.
Pour cake batter over all.
Cook at 350° approximately 30 to 40 minutes, then let sit in oven at low temperature (150°) for 20 minutes.

title: raspberry crunch
directions: Mix with blender and fork and press in a 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch pan.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: gingerbread(recipe is 121 years old)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and blend in eggs. Add flour to which spices have been added.
Add flour and soda mixture with buttermilk alternately.
Cook in greased sheath pan in 350° for about 25 minutes.
Serve with applesauce.

title: raisin pecan oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Add flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in oats, raisins and pecans.

title: strawberry pie(easy)
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add water; cook on medium until boiling (stirring constantly).
Remove from heat and add jello and let cool.
Place berries in cooled and cooked pie shell.
Pour jello mixture over.
Refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: spoon rolls
directions: *May substitute plain flour and add 2 tablespoons baking powder and 2 teaspoons salt.

title: refrigerator yeast rolls
directions: Mix salt, sugar, boiling water and Crisco; stir until dissolved.
Cool to lukewarm.
Mix yeast and 1/2 cup lukewarm water until dissolved, then add to first mixture.
Add beaten egg; mix well.
Stir in flour to make soft dough.
Cover tightly; store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Will keep 1 week.
When ready, pull off pieces the size of egg.
Roll in hands and place in greased pan.
Cover with cloth and let rise until double in size (1 hour).
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: deer stew
directions: In an 8-quart Dutch oven over medium heat in oil, cook deer meat, a few pieces at a time, until well browned on all sides. Remove meat as it browns; set it aside.
In drippings, cook sliced onion until lightly brown, about 3 minutes.
Return meat to oven; add 1/4 cup water, vinegar, salt and sugar and heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 2 hours, turning meat occasionally and adding more water if needed.
Add vegetables and continue cooking 1 1/2 hours until meat and vegetables are fork-tender.
Remove meat and vegetables to warm platter.
Skim fat from pan liquid.
In a cup, blend flour and 1/2 cup water until smooth; slowly stir into hot liquid in Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, until mixture is thickened.
Serve gravy over meat and vegetables.

title: vegetable-barley soup
directions: Brown meat.
Add onions and garlic.
Cook until onions are tender.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and boil for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add 6 tablespoons sugar. Spread on cooked pie.
Bake until brown.

title: confetti apple slaw
directions: In a large bowl, stir together juice and apples.
Add cabbage, onion, pepper and raisins.
In a small bowl, stir together mayonnaise, yogurt, mustard, pepper and paprika.
Add to vegetable mixture.
Cover tightly and refrigerate until served.

title: hunter's pie
directions: Combine vegetables and water, bring to boil, cook 8 minutes. Drain, reserving 1 1/2 cups liquid, set aside.

title: beef flavored rice
directions: Put rice in dish.
Pour over consomme and bouillon soup.
Add butter. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese sauce dip
directions: Melt cheese.
Add Ro-Tel.
Diced jalapeno peppers may also be added for extra "heat".

title: stuffed turkey breast
directions: Punch 5 or 6 holes in turkey breast and stuff with garlic and onions.
Sprinkle with small amount of salt.
In browning bag, pour Catalina dressing, Mrs. Dash steak sauce, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Place turkey in bag.
Seal and shake to coat with sauce.
Marinate overnight.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° or cook in slow cooker with 1 1/2 cups water until done.

title: loaded potato soup
directions: Finely dice potatoes and onions.
Boil until done.
Reduce heat to low.
Add cheese soup and mix well.
Cut cream cheese into cubes and add to mixture.
Heat mixture until cream cheese is completely blended.
Serve hot.

title: old-fashioned egg noodles
directions: Mix flour in until real stiff, then roll out real thin. Sprinkle with flour to keep from sticking and roll up.
Slice off with sharp knife 1/8-inch slices.
Pull apart and let dry 3 days. Serves about 6.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix rhubarb, granulated sugar and lemon juice and rind. Spread in bottom of 8-inch square glass dish. Mix together brown sugar, flour and butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle on top of rhubarb.
Bake in microwave for about 15 minutes, turning dish 90 degrees every 4 minutes.
Test center of crisp with fork.
If rhubarb is tender, remove from microwave.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream (or nothing if you prefer).

title: pineapple cherry surprise!
directions: Pour pineapple and cherries into bottom of a 9 x 2 x 11-inch pan. Cover with uncooked yellow cake mix. Cover cake mix with pats of margarine.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until top is golden brown.

title: squirrel
directions: Heat shortening in frying pan.
Roll squirrel in flour.
Place in pan.
Sprinkle on salt and pepper.
Cook on medium heat, turning as needed until real tender and brown.
Remove from pan. Serve or can make gravy in grease.

title: pronto taco soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook beef, onion and garlic until meat is no longer pink; drain.
Add the broth, tomatoes, picante sauce, pasta, green pepper, chili powder, parsley and taco seasoning. Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 10-15 minutes or until pasta is tender.
Garnish with cheese and tortilla chips.
Yield:
8 servings (2 qts.).

title: broccoli casserole(or squash)
directions: Cook broccoli or squash and onion in butter.
Add milk, salt, pepper and eggs.
Sprinkle with crumbs; top with cheese.
Bake in oven for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Chill the first 3 ingredients 1 hour, mixed and covered.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss in dressing.

title: baked sliced potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Place slices, overlapping, in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix butter and oil.
Brush or dip slices of potatoes with mixture. Sprinkle with garlic and spices. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Slice bananas and place in pie crust.
Beat Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk with lemon juice.
Spread over bananas.
Drain pineapple and spread over mixture.
Spread on Cool Whip.
Place cherries and pecans on top.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream the first 5 ingredients.
Add the peanut butter and stir well.
Add the baking soda and oats.
Stir by hand with a large sturdy scraper.
Add M&M's, chips and nuts. Stir well.
Can refrigerate in a tightly sealed container.
Drop by teaspoonful on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, but do not overbake.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Thoroughly blend all ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes, then at 350° for 20 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Makes 1 pie.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix
all ingredients and let come to a boil.
Let cool. Mix with fresh strawberries and put in baked (cool) pie shell. Top with cream.

title: potato salad with sour cream
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Garnish
with sliced boiled eggs. Cover and chill.

title: fiesta coleslaw
directions: Cover green and red cabbage with cold water combined with 1 teaspoon salt.
Let soak 1 hour.
In large bowl, combine mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar and remaining salt.
Add drained cabbage, carrot, olives and green pepper; toss lightly. Refrigerate, covered,
several hours before serving.

title: a raw vegetable plate
directions: Place
all
prepared vegetables on a large platter that has been covered with lettuce leaves.
Serves 8 to 10.
Serve with any meal.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in pan and bake until golden brown for 25 minutes.
Cut in triangles (2 x 1-inch), if desired.

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Boil carrots in salt water until tender and cool.
Alternate carrots, pepper and onions in dish.
Combine remaining ingredients, beat until well blended and pour over vegetables and refrigerate.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cereal and nuts.
Combine egg, oil, water, bananas and vanilla. Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir just to moisten.
Spread evenly into pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.
Let cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together real well.
Fold in hash browns which have been partially thawed.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with 1 1/2 cups crushed cornflakes mixed with 1 stick melted margarine.
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes in a preheated oven at 350°.

title: country dumplings
directions: Drop by spoonfuls into chicken stew.
Dip spoon into boiled stew first (the dough will slide off easier).
Cover pan and cook 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: In a small saucepan, combine sugar, butter and milk.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate pieces until smooth.
Pour over partially cooled cake. Cut into squares immediately after frosting.
This is a moist cake.
Covered, it keeps well in a cool place.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Sift together sugar and cocoa.
Add salt, melted butter and eggs.
Add milk.
Mix well.
Pour equally into 2 Johnson's Redicrust graham cracker shells.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until firm.
Chill and serve with Cool Whip.

title: refrigerator potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes, drain and add sour cream, cream cheese, onion salt, butter, salt and pepper.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Combine Jello with water per package instructions.
Stir in remaining ingredients and congeal.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease 2 loaf pans. Beat all ingredients in a large bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly 30 seconds. Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl frequently, 45 seconds. Pour into pans. Bake until wooden pick inserted halfway in center and sides come out clean (50 to 60 minutes). Cool completely before slicing.

title: holiday lemonade
directions: In
punch
bowl,
combine lemonade, orange juice, sparkling water,
and ginger ale.
Stir until blended.
Add strawberries. Serve at once.
Makes 24 punch cup servings.

title: baked beans deluxe
directions: Saute onions in bacon drippings.
Combine all ingredients except bacon in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and mix well.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: salmon balls
directions: Heat oil in small saucepan while preparing salmon.
Pan should be 1/2 full of oil.
Drain salmon, saving juice.
Add flour and egg to salmon.
Add heaping teaspoon baking powder to salmon juice. Let foam 30 seconds, then pour back over salmon.
Drop by teaspoons into oil; fry until brown.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate chip treasure cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°. In small bowl, mix graham cracker crumbs, flour and baking powder. In large mixer bowl, beat condensed milk and butter until smooth. Add graham cracker crumb mixture. Mix well. Stir in coconut, chocolate chips and walnuts. Drop by rounded tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake 9 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Store, loosely covered, at room temperature. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients well. Bake at 350° (uncovered) for 30 minutes, or until casserole starts to bubble. Top with bread crumbs and serve.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together in large bowl, butter, brown sugar, sugar, vanilla and egg.
In separate bowl, combine flour, soda and salt. Gradually add to other mixture, stirring after each addition.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a Pyrex pie dish. In top of a double boiler, melt chocolate with butter. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients; pour into pie dish. Bake at 350° for 20 - 30 minutes, until a toothpick inserted in center comes out almost clean. Cool on wire rack. Serve with ice cream.

title: ooey goey cake
directions: Mix all together and pour over crumble mix.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 325° oven.
Cake will rise then go flat during baking.

title: pearadise jam
directions: Combine fruits.
Add pectin over high heat and stir to boiling.
Add sugar and bring to rolling boil for 2 minutes.
Stir after removing from heat.
Ladle into hot, sterilized jars and seal.

title: easy yellow daisy cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add shortening, milk (2/3) and vanilla.
Mix until smooth stiff batter.
Add eggs and 1/3 milk. Mix to smooth batter. Pour into 2 (8-inch) greased cake pans. Cool and ice.

title: fish chowder(from a maine recipe)
directions: Saute several slices of diced bacon until crisp; set aside. Saute onion in part of the fat.
Add potatoes.
Cover and cook until tender in boiling water.
Add pieces of whitefish, raw or previously cooked.
Add milk or half and half.
Season with salt and pepper or bouillon cubes.
Serve with diced bacon sprinkled on top of chowder.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large mixer bowl, beat condensed milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Add Bisquick baking mix and vanilla.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with fork. Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: artichoke cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 5 x 9-inch baking dish. Cook at 325° for 45 minutes. Serve warm with crackers or fresh bread.

title: strawberry-angel food dessert
directions: Cut angel food cake into small cubes.
Place in a large 4-cup serving bowl and set aside.
Combine sour cream, milk and powdered sugar, stirring until smooth.

title: grilled sweet corn with garlic butter
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion. Saute until glazed, but not browned, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add rice. Toss with a fork 2 to 3 minutes until rice is glazed.
Pour in wine and 2 1/2 cups broth.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer until rice is tender and broth is absorbed, about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate drop oatmeal candy
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk.
Boil over hot flame until it reaches rolling boil that cannot be stirred down.
Add vanilla. Beat, add oats and any other extras.
Drop quickly on greased sheets to cool.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen teaspoon-sized drops.

title: pizzelles
directions: Beat eggs with mixer.
Add oil and beat until creamy. Gradually add sugar and all other ingredients at low speed.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Mix eggs, oil and water together.
Add to flour.
Separate dough into 3 balls.
Roll out very thin on floured board.
Let set 20 minutes.
Boil chicken breasts until tender; debone.
In broth, add cans of broth, oleo and oil.
Bring to boil. Drop in dumplings.
Cook on medium heat about 30 minutes, uncovered.
Let set for 1 to 2 hours before eating.

title: easy turkey pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pinch off 1/4 of dough from first loaf and add to second.
Roll out this larger piece of dough on a floured board to fit inside and up edges of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Stretch dough to fit pan.
Set aside.

title: special potato soup
directions: Cook all ingredients, except cheese and milk. Remove from heat and mash vegetables slightly.
Add milk and thicken.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Combine brown sugar and butter in an 8-inch frying pan or cake pan.
Stir over low heat until thoroughly mixed.
Arrange fruit in this mixture. Stir sugar slowly into beaten egg yolks and add hot water slowly. Beat well.
Add vanilla and sifted dry ingredients, mixing well. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: pear bread
directions: Grate the 2 pears.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add oil, sugar, lemon peel, vanilla and pears.
Mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 or 3 loaf pans and bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: biscotta
directions: Cream butter, add sugar and eggs and beat. Add vanilla and baking powder.
Make a well, knead and shape into S and O.
Bake approximately 10 minutes at 400°.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Mix pudding until thick using 3 cups milk.
Spread on previous mixture.
Then spread Cool Whip over top and sprinkle nuts or grated chocolate over top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: arabian squash-cheese casserole
directions: Cut the squash down the middle; scoop out seeds and place it face down in an oiled pan.
Bake at 375° for about 35 minutes, until soft.
Cool; scoop out seeds and mash.
Saute the onion and garlic in butter.
When the onion is translucent, add the chopped peppers.
Saute until peppers are just underdone.
Beat eggs with buttermilk or yogurt.
Crumble in Feta cheese.
Combine everything and mix well.
Add salt, peppers or hot sauce to taste.
Spread into buttered casserole.
Top with seeds or nuts and bake at 375°, covered 25 minutes and uncovered 10 minutes.

title: lemon fluff cake
directions: Make cake according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool.
Poke cake with fork.
Mix jello with 1 cup hot water and 1/2 cup cold.
Put jello in refrigerator for 1/2 hour. Spoon over cooled cake.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Chop cauliflower into small flowerets.
Combine mayonnaise, celery salt and garlic salt.
Mix with remaining ingredients and refrigerate several hours.

title: green, white and gold casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine until clear; do not brown.
Add cream of chicken soup; blend well.
Mix all other ingredients.
Place in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Cover top with shredded cheese. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: jon's tea
directions: Place all tea bags in 6 to 8 cups of water.
Place in microwave oven and cook on High for 13 minutes.
Let steep 1 to 2 hours.
Remove tea bags (do not squeeze bags as they will make your tea bitter) and pour contents into a 1 gallon pitcher. Finish filling pitcher with cold water and sweeten to taste.
Pour into glass filled with ice and enjoy!

title: creme brulee canadienne custard(a classic french dessert)
directions: Heat in top of a double boiler the cream.
Beat together egg yolks and granulated sugar; gradually beat in hot cream.
Blend in vanilla.
Pour into flat-bottomed 2-quart casserole and set in pan of hot water.
Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until set.
Sprinkle top with 1/3 cup maple sugar; broil for 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve chilled.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli-cheese soup no. 2
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain completely.
Put back into pan.
Add half and half; heat slowly. Cut cheese into chunks and add broccoli mixture.
Stir until cheese melts.
Do not boil.

title: shrimp marinated in mustard dill sauce
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together in blender.
Process until smooth.
Stir this sauce into shrimp.
Refrigerate and serve on lettuce with tomatoes.
Use dill as an extra garnish.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Five minutes before done, sprinkle rest of French onions on top.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine margarine, oil, eggs, sugars and vanilla.
Mix well and set aside.

title: easy punch
directions: Put
sherbet
in punch bowl.
Pour Sprite over sherbet. Pale, lovely
shade
of
green.
To have other pastel colors, change from lime to any flavor you choose.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon of oil and fry eggs on both sides.
Remove eggs and shred.
Heat remaining oil and brown onion and rice.
Add shrimp, stirring while cooking until they turn pink.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well until thoroughly heated, about 5 to 8 minutes.
Serve topped with shredded eggs.
Makes 6 servings.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter well.
Stir in eggs and sour cream. Add the dry ingredients which have been sifted together and vanilla.
Mix well.
Chill several hours.
May be dropped or rolled and cut 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle with sugar or cinnamon sugar.
Top with nuts or raisins (optional).
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: easy cheesy buns
directions: Add gradually 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 cups flour to form dough.
Mix well after each addition.
Fill well-greased muffin pan 1/2 full. Cover and let raise in warm place until light and doubled in size, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 375° in oven 12 to 15 minutes or until deep brown.
Makes 1 dozen rolls.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze thawed frozen spinach by hand or in paper toweling to remove all moisture.
Combine spinach, sour cream, yogurt, parsley, green onion, salt and pepper to taste in a small bowl.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours or overnight to blend flavors.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, water, ketchup and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients to taste.
Thickens while it cooks.
Great with chicken or steak.

title: egg-sausage casserole
directions: Fry and drain sausage, crumble.
In large bowl, beat eggs and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered 7 x 11 inch pan and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, until bubbly and lightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: do not stir peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter
in deep baking dish.
Beat the ingredients together, then
pour over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Add at least 3
cups
peaches (or whatever fruit you prefer).
Do not stir.
Sprinkle over this
1 cup sugar.
Do not stir.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: party corn
directions: Beat eggs. Add sour cream, then the corn and muffin mix. Add butter last. Grease 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until center is set.

title: marinated round roast
directions: Cut round roast into 1-inch cubes; set aside.
Combine Zinfandel, garlic, oregano and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Add marinade to round roast.
Marinate overnight.
Prepare using any favorite roast recipe.

title: mock cherry pie
directions: Pour the hot water over the raisins and cranberries and cook until the cranberries burst, then add the sugar and flour.
Take from stove.
Add vanilla.
Bake with two crusts.
This makes 1 pie.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound each chicken breast flat; salt and pepper.
Place 1 slice cheese and ham on chicken breast and roll up; secure with toothpick.
Add oil to bottom of frypan; slowly brown the chicken pieces on all sides.
Remove from pan; drain oil from pan.
Pour cream of chicken soup and 1/2 cup milk into the pan; stir on medium heat until sauce loosens.
Add finely chopped onion; simmer 10 minutes.
Add chicken breasts to sauce; spoon sauce over chicken.
Heat/simmer 15 minutes or until tender.
Makes 4 generous servings.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Wash and stem strawberries.
Put in bowl with cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice.
Crush together with pastry blender until well blended.
Stir in drained fruit cocktail.
Whip cream until stiff.
Fold into fruit mixture.
Pour into quart containers and freeze.

title: pineapple nut salad
directions: Dissolve jello	in
hot
water.
Blend in cream cheese. Add all other ingredients.
Pour into mold and congeal.

title: cooked cheese spread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let set 1/2 to 1 hour over low heat.
Melt butter/margarine and add flour to make a paste.
Add other mixture and cook until melted and creamy.
Add caraway seed and put into buttered dish.
Serve with crackers.

title: best pancakes
directions: Beat together liquid ingredients.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to liquid ingredients; mix well. Cook on hot griddle until both sides are golden brown.
Makes 10 pancakes.

title: oatmeal hotcakes
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Cook over moderate heat.
Serves 4.

title: coconut bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients like pie crust and put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread out evenly and bake 10 minutes at 350°. Have ready the remaining ingredients.
Mix the rest of ingredients together well and pour over first mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Mix all filling ingredients in a bowl.
Pour into the unbaked pie shell.
Dot with butter and pour cup of boiling water over the mixture.
Put on top crust and bake at 425 F for 30 minutes.
This tastes surprisingly like apple pie.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Mix pineapple and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Add jello; dissolve and then add 2 cups cold water.
Chill until thick.
Fold in cheese, nuts and Cool Whip.

title: oatmeal refrigerator cookies
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients.
Mix shortening with next 6 ingredients.
Mix in flour mixture, then oats.
Press and mold into 2 rolls. Wrap and chill.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°. Yields 4 dozen.

title: butter pecan dessert
directions: Mix flour, chopped nuts and melted margarine.
Place in a deep baking dish and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: italian spaghetti muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Line 6 giant muffin cups with foil.
Spray foil with nonstick cooking spray.
In a large bowl stir together warm spaghetti and margarine.
Add Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Then toss with a fork to combine.
Divide spaghetti mixture and spoon into bottom of muffin cups forming a nest. Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti (about 1 1/2 Tbsp. per muffin).
Set aside.

title: apple or cherry nut crunch
directions: Spread pie filling in Pyrex baking dish.
Pour lemon juice over fruit filling.
Mix cake mix, margarine and nuts together. Sprinkle over top of fruit filling.
Bake until brown.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions in 2 tablespoons butter; remove from pan. Trim fat and bone from steak. Cut into strips.

Melt additional butter (2 tablespoons) in pan. Toss strips of meat in flour. Brown meat in butter. Add salt and bouillon cubes. Simmer, stirring occasionally, until meat is tender, about 1 1/4 hours. Add mushrooms, onions and sour cream. Heat and serve over noodles or rice. Serves 6.

title: caramel cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Bet eggs and add other ingredients, mixing well and adding nuts last.
Roll into 2 long rolls and refrigerate overnight.
Slice and bake as needed.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Butter must be used instead of shortening.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend all together and refrigerate.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Wash and slice potatoes like chips (leave skins on).
Preheat shallow pan with 2 tablespoons oil/butter.
Layer potatoes. Season with salt and pepper. Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.
Remove and turn potatoes over. Bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes. Before removing, you may sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: sirloin tips over noodles
directions: Roll tips in flour and salt.
Pan-fry onions and garlic in oil. Remove and add meat, browning evenly.
Place meat in casserole dish.
Combine 2 tablespoons flour with drippings in pan.
Add beef broth and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook until thickened.
Add onions, mushrooms and garlic and pour over beef tips.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°, covered.
When done, mix sour cream with gravy in casserole and reheat.
Serve over hot noodles.
Add a little sour cream to moisten and flavor noodles.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, mustard and salt.
Sprinkle one side of beef steak with half the mixture.
Pound in.
Repeat on other side.
Cut beef into 6 pieces.
Heat oil in 10-inch skillet.
Cook beef over medium heat until brown.
Add tomatoes and garlic.
Break up tomatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer until beef is tender (approximately 1 1/4 hours).

title: creamy mashed potatoes
directions: Heat water, salt and butter to a boil; remove from heat.
Stir in milk and flakes.
Add mayonnaise and whip until creamy.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel potatoes; grate or run through fine food chopper.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Heat oil in a skillet.
Spoon batter into skillet until brown on one side, then flip over and brown on other side.
Drain on paper towel and serve hot.
Amount of flour will vary with the water content of potatoes.

title: poor man steak
directions: Mix all, but mushroom soup, and mold in a loaf pan. Refrigerate overnight.
Unmold and slice mixture.
Fry until brown on both sides.
Put in baking dish.
Mix 2 cans of mushroom soup with two cups of water; mix well.
Pour over sliced meat in baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: round's spicy chicken and pasta
directions: In a 4-quart skillet, saute chicken, jalapeno pepper, cayenne pepper, salt and garlic in oil for approximately 20 minutes.
Add chopped broccoli and continue cooking until broccoli is tender. Stir occasionally.
When broccoli is tender, cook pasta according to directions.
Drain pasta leaving some water on the bottom of the pan.
Add oil and additional garlic to the pasta.
Toss in the chicken and broccoli.
Serve.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Cook chicken in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sanders chocolate pie
directions: Bring to boil or cook until thick on low to medium heat.
Fill a baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Bake until brown.

title: butterscotch apple
directions: In large bowl, combine lemon juice and apples; toss until coated.
Stir in sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover edges with aluminum foil.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: ceviche
directions: Dice fillets into dime-size pieces and place in a glass bowl. Cover pieces with lime juice and marinate for 4 to 5 hours at room temperature.
Drain pieces and blot off excess lime juice. Combine pieces with remaining ingredients; mix well in a glass bowl.
Cover and refrigerate mixture until cold, then serve as a salad or hors d'oeuvre.

title: maryland biscuits
directions: Stir dry ingredients, cut in lard until mixture looks like cornmeal, add water, making up small portions at a time.
Knead mixture well, then place on biscuit board and hammer 1/2 hour. Turn dough during beating, cover with damp cloth and make out biscuits.
Bake in hot oven at 450° to 475° for 17 to 20 minutes.

title: kyle smith drink
directions: Fill tall glass with ice. Pour in apple and peach schnapps. Then fill up with soda.

title: mr. rash's guacamole dip
directions: Remove skins and pits from avocado and put the pulp in large bowl.
Slice olives.
Wash mushrooms, tomatoes and
onions and chop into desired size of pieces.
Smash avocados until smooth in bowl.
Add lemon juice.
Add vegetables, reserving a few to garnish with later.
Add seasonings.
Stir enough mayonnaise to form a dip consistency.
Stir in approximately 8 ounces of salsa. Stir mixture.
Make small indentation in center of dip.
Fill "pool" with remaining salsa.
Garnish with remaining vegetables.

title: simply elegant steak and rice
directions: In large skillet, brown meat in oil, using high heat.
Add onions; saute until tender-crisp.
Blend soup, bouillon, liquid from mushrooms and garlic salt; pour over steak.
Add mushrooms. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 hour or until steak is tender. Serve over beds of fluffy rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour Western dressing over the top. Serve immediately.
Enjoy!

title: noodle kugel
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil noodles.
Beat eggs and add with other ingredients to noodles.
Place 3 or 4 tablespoons margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan and melt.
Add kugel mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm.
Excellent with fish or pot roast. Serves 10 to 12.

title: spiced dogs
directions: In crock-pot, place jellies, sauce and mustard, then cook on low heat until melted.
Add frank slices (in 1/2-inch pieces).
Let cook on low heat for a few hours.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar in a mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Blend in bananas, buttermilk and vanilla.

title: palacinky(blintzes)
directions: Pour just enough batter in a crepe pan to cover the bottom. Carefully turn when brown.
Fill with whatever you wish.
My family's favorite is strawberry jam and cottage cheese.
Makes approximately 10.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Mix well and pour batter in baking dish.
Pour fruit on top of batter.
Bake at 350° until batter raises up through fruit and browns on top.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: In a small bowl, put flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, cream together sugars and butter, then add eggs, one at a time, then vanilla.
Mix well. Stir in oatmeal and flour mixture.
Add chips and nuts.
Drop from spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 7 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 dozen.

title: routh's oriental chicken casserole
directions: Saut in butter the onion, bell pepper and celery and set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine the soup, mayonnaise, milk and soy sauce.
Add chicken with lemon juice sprinkled over the top, rice, cheese and English peas or snow peas.
Add the sauted vegetables and mix together.
Spray large baking dish or 2 smaller dishes with Pam and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until completely hot.
Cover with crushed potato chips and bake 10 more minutes. Freezes well.

title: rhubarb custard cake dessert
directions: Mix lemon cake mix (not pudding type, if possible) according to package directions.
Pour in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
On top of this, put cut up rhubarb. Sprinkle with white sugar.
Pour whipping cream over top.
Bake for 45 minutes or until cake is done.
The topping sinks to the bottom and forms a layer of custard and the cake ends up on top.

title: veggie bars
directions: Pat crescent rolls in jelly roll pan or 2 (9 x 13-inch) Pyrex pans.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes until lightly brown.
Cool. Mix salad dressing, sour cream, cream cheese and Ranch mix. Spread on cool crust.
Mix veggies and spread on top of cheese.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown steak and onion in margarine.
Stir in soup, water and paprika.
Cover.
Cook 30 minutes on low.
Add sour cream and cook 15 more minutes.
Stir often.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: caramely butter toffee
directions: Combine sugar, salt, water and margarine.
Cook to light crack stage (286°).
Add walnuts to toffee.
Pour onto well-greased cookie sheet and cool.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over toffee.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Break into pieces when cooled.

title: spinach squares
directions: Butter a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
In a large bowl, beat eggs well; add flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add cheese, spinach and onion.
Mix well.
Spoon into a baking dish and level.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool for approximately 45 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for 4 to 6 hours before serving.

title: curried tomatoes
directions: Heat butter, oil, curry powder and sugar. Add the onion and cook until soft. Add the tomatoes and cook for 3 minutes. Makes approximately 8 servings.

title: delicious ritz chocolate dessert
directions: Mix crackers, baking powder, vanilla and walnuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff and gradually add sugar while beating.
Combine and stir egg mixture with crackers mixture.
Pour into greased deep pie dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Whip cream until stiff and stir in grated Hershey bar.
Spread over top.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain squash well.
Mix all ingredients, except dressing and margarine.
Make alternate layers of squash and dressing, ending up with dressing on top.
Melt margarine and pour over the top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Servings for 8.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mandarin oranges to make 2 cups of juice. Can use a little orange juice, if not enough juices.
Make pudding according to package, but use juices in place of milk.
Stir.
Add pineapple and oranges.
Stir again.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or more.
Add bananas in and stir before serving.

title: double corn brunch bake
directions: In medium saucepan over medium heat, cook onion in oil, stirring occasionally, until tender, 4 to 5 minutes.

title: maple nut divinity
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in buttered, large, glass mixing bowl.
Microwave for 15 to 17 minutes on Roast or until candy forms a hard ball in cold water (250°).

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add graham cracker crumbs, tossing to coat well with butter.
Set aside. Place cottage cheese, sour cream and cream cheese together in mixing bowl.
Blend with electric mixer.
Add sugar, then eggs and vanilla.
Blend with electric mixer or food processor and blend 1 minute.
Line mini muffin pans with paper liners.
Place 1 teaspoon of graham cracker crumbs in each liner.
Press down firmly.
Fill liners 3/4 full with cheese mixture.
Bake exactly 12 minutes.
Let cool, then top each with 1 teaspoon pie filling. Chill until topping sets.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: baked beans for a crowd
directions: Combine all ingredients except for the bacon.
Top with the bacon.
Cover and bake at 350° until mixture bubbles and thickens.

title: 3 minute fudge
directions: Mix milk, sugar and salt.
Bring to a slow boil. Boil 3 minutes. Remove from heat. Add marshmallows, chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts.
Stir until melted.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan. Refrigerate until firm.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into buttered casserole; do not make too deep.
Top with 1/2 cup buttered bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: grits casserole
directions: *This cheese is not available, so use 4 or 5 ounces grated Cheddar cheese and add garlic powder.

title: chinese cole slaw
directions: Mix cole slaw, onions, sunflower seeds, almonds, and noodles, set aside. Mix oil, sugar, vinegar, seasoning packet together and refrigerate 1/2 hour. Pour dressing over salad and serve.

title: chili con queso
directions: Melt together all ingredients. Serve in a chafing dish. Sprinkle with paprika. Serve with Doritos or Fritos.

title: oven fries
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Spray 9 x 13-inch baking dish with cooking spray. Scrub potatoes thoroughly, leaving skin on. Slice potatoes in "French fry" style. Place potatoes in pan and sprinkle generously with garlic powder. Lightly dust potatoes with comino and paprika. Spray potatoes with cooking spray. Bake for 40 to 60 minutes, depending on number of potatoes (more time for more potatoes). Stir potatoes carefully once or twice during baking time. Spray again with cooking spray if potatoes look dry. Makes 6 servings.

title: mint cream frosting
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer; gradually add sugar, beating after each addition.
Add milk; beat until spreading consistency.
Stir in peppermint extract and food coloring.
Yields about 2 cups.

title: meat scramble
directions: Stir and brown ground beef and 1-1/2 tsp. of salt.
Chop course in food grinder or food processor potatoes, carrots and onions and add to browned meat mixture.
Add 1 tsp. salt, pepper and milk.
Cover and cook slowly 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir occasionally, adding more milk if needed. Continue cooking uncovered about 3 minutes longer or until thick.

title: smothered steak
directions: Put steak strips, flour, salt and pepper in crock-pot.
Stir well to coat steak.
Add all remaining ingredients, except rice. Cover and cook on high for 1 hour, then low for 8 hours (can do on high for 5 hours).
Serve over hot rice.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add sugar and oil; beat eggs and add to the mixture.
Add carrots and blend. Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Heat cream, cheeses and butter over low heat until melted. Place potatoes in greased 9 x 13-inch pan; let thaw.
One hour before baking, pour cheese mixture over thawed potatoes to just the top of potatoes.
Do not mix.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: sugar free lemon pie
directions: Combine dry lemonade and pudding mixes in a large bowl.
With mixer on low speed, add 2 c of milk to the dry ingredients.
In a small bowl, beat the cream cheese and 1 c milk until smooth.
Add cream cheese mixture to the pudding mixture.
Fold in pineapple. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 2 prepared pie shells.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Yield:
2 pies.

title: layered orange salad
directions: Dissolve sugar and flour in little juice and gradually add rest of juice and egg yolk until thickens.
Add 2 tablespoons butter; stir well and cool mixture in cold water (use metal bowl for mixture and place bowl in larger metal or glass bowl with ice cubes and water to cool quickly).
To this cooled mixture, add the 1/2 pint whipped whipping cream.
Then spread this mixture over congealed jello mixture made with lemon jello, orange jello, bananas, crushed pineapple and nuts.
Top with grated cheese.
Very festive.
Great for holidays!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix eggs, soup, onion and mayo in bowl (add broccoli).
Put in casserole.
Top with cheese.
Melt butter; mix with bread crumbs and put on cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Beat with wire whisk and pour over cabbage, etc.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 13x9-inch baking pan; set aside.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Line muffin tin.
Place one vanilla wafer in each liner.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla and sugar until well blended.
Add eggs. Mix well.
Pour over wafers, filling 3/4 full.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Remove from pan when cool.
Chill.
Decorate how you choose.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; place 1/2 of this mix into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dip flour tortillas into warm chicken broth.
Place over chicken mixture.
Repeat so there is two layers.
Top with cheese, garlic salt and chili powder.
Mix soups and chicken broth.
Spread this over layers of chicken and tortillas, then pour Ro-Tel tomatoes over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: great chili
directions: Saute meat and onions together until the red is out of meat, then drain.
Add remaining ingredients to meat.
Cook slowly.
If too thin, add cornstarch.

title: onion-chive butter
directions: Blend onion, chives and butter.
Form into a roll, about 1 inch in diameter.
Chill.
Cut into small disks.
Makes about 2/3 cup.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Combine potatoes and onion.
Squeeze out all excess liquid. Mix in eggs, salt, pepper, flour and baking powder.
Let rest 5 minutes.
Heat butter and oil on griddle over medium heat.
Drop batter by tablespoonful.
Flatten with back of spoon.
Fry on both sides until dark golden brown.

title: lemon squares
directions: Cream together margarine, 1/2 cup powdered sugar and 2 cups flour together in a fine crumbly state.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook and stir onion in butter until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except shrimp and rice.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes.
Stir in shrimp; heat through.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cook sliced peaches in the water until soft.
In separate bowl, mix sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt.
When peaches are soft, put in a large baking dish and spoon around flour mixture. Mixture will rise.
Bake at 400° for about 40 minutes or until it forms a brown crust.

title: banana split fun
directions: In a mixing bowl, toss together the graham cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Press mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a small bowl, beat the remaining 1/2 cup butter until softened; add powdered sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Spread this mixture over crumbs.
Slice bananas and arrange over this mixture. Spoon pineapple over bananas, then spread thawed whipped topping over this.
Decorate with chocolate and cherries; refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer ingredients on a pizza or in a flat dish from bottom up in the order given.
Chill and serve with taco chips, Doritos or Fritos.

title: mrs. loop's chicken
directions: Boil chicken with onion, carrot and celery.
Debone.
Melt butter in skillet.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook until bubbly.
Add milk and chicken broth.
Bring to boil.
Boil one minute stirring constantly.
Add chicken, cream of mushroom soup, green pepper and rice.
Stir and pour into greased baking dish. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix together, then add 1 cup chopped pecans.
Press in 2 pie pans or long baking dish and brown in oven.

title: crab casserole supreme
directions: Mix ingredients.
Top with 1/2 cup bread crumbs, mixed into 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.
Mix crumbs into casserole and bake another 20 minutes or until done.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pastry pie shell and bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: turtle candies
directions: Microwave chocolate chips in a glass bowl on High for 1 1/2 minutes, stirring after one minute.
Stir until smooth.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Drop chocolate by tablespoons onto a wax paper lined baking sheet, shaping into 16 (1 1/2-inch) circles.
Reserve remaining chocolate.
Arrange 4 pecans over each circle.
Chill and firm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients; shape into a large ball.
Roll in pecans that have been chopped very fine (1 cup).

title: black and red peppered shrimp
directions: In heavy skillet, melt butter over medium-high heat.
Add peppers and shrimp.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add garlic; cook about 1 minute.
Add lemon juice.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6 people as appetizer with crusty bread.
Serves 2 people as main course.

title: mom and dad's chili
directions: In a larger saucepan brown ground beef; add onion and bell pepper.
Saute until limp.
Add chili powder and mix well.
Add remaining spices, tomato sauce, tomato paste and 1 cup water.
Add canned beans or cooked beans and simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Ladle off any excess grease at top.
Serve with crackers or jalapeno cornbread.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix bananas with baking soda in mixing bowl, let stand for several min. Combine sugar, shortening, and eggs in mixing bowl. Beat until smooth. Add banana mixture, flour and salt, alternating. Mix well after each addition. Fold in pecans. Spoon into a greased and flour loaf pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour. Remove to cool.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Put in a greased iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and place in shallow casserole.
Combine pineapple juice, sugar, flour and egg in small saucepan and cook over medium heat until slightly thickened.
Sprinkle grated cheese, marshmallows and sage over pineapple.
Last, pour sauce over all. Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Roast at 375° for 1 hour.
Turn oven off for 3 hours.
After 3 hours, turn oven back on at 375° for 1/2 hour (rare) or 10 minutes more for medium rare.
Do not peek in oven at any time.
Timing should be exact, otherwise, it will smoke.

title: brownies from homemade mix
directions: In bowl, combine first 4 ingredients and mix until smooth. Spread into greased 8-inch square
pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into squares while still warm.
Sprinkle on confectioners sugar if desired.
Yields 9 brownies.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows; stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat. Add cereal; stir until well coated.
Using a buttered spatula or waxed paper, press mixture evenly into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan coated with cooking spray or margarine.
Cut into squares when cool.
Yields 24 treats.

title: hot broccoli and cheese dip
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of water, just to thaw; drain. Saute onion in oleo.
Melt cheese in onion mixture.
Stir in mushrooms, soup and broccoli.
Serve hot.
Thin with small amount of milk if necessary.

title: raisin bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs for 5 minutes.
Add vanilla, flour, baking powder and canned milk.
Add raisins.
Add nuts and candied fruit if desired.
Pour into 3 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 250° approximately 2 1/4 to to 2 1/2 hours.

title: banana oatmeal bars
directions: Mix. Spread in 9 x 13-inch well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: Mix dry ingredients with prepared mustard.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add vinegars to egg yolk mixture and when thoroughly combined, add oil, very slowly at first.
Continue adding oil until all 2 cups are in.
Beat entire time and let's hope you have an electric mixer for this job!
It is delicious!
Try it soon.

title: fat free bran muffins
directions: Mix together milk and fruit spread.
Add and mix with egg product.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Add raisins.
Pour in muffin tins sprayed with Pam.
Bake 23 minutes at 350° or until brown and firm to touch.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, Karo and water.
Stir over low flame until sugar melts.
Turn flame higher and cook until it spins a 6 or 7-inch thread (238°).
Add peanuts and cook slowly until it turns to a golden brown.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, salt and soda. While still foaming, pour on a greased cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Mix flour and dry ingredients.
Beat eggs.
Add lard to dry ingredients. Mix well to make a soft dough.
Let set in refrigerator for 2 hours or overnight.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in 4 to 5 rounds and put in filling on half and wet edge with milk.
Fold the other half over and press with fork. Fry in 400° shortening until brown on both sides. Makes 12 to 14 pies.

title: liver and onions
directions: Salt and pepper liver.
Roll in flour.
Put oil in skillet over medium heat.
Place liver and cut up onion in pan.
Fry until brown on both sides, but not too brown.
Sprinkle a little more flour in pan.
Add water and simmer until gravy is thick.

title: peach pie
directions: Butter casserole.
Mix peaches or blackberries.
Mix flour with fruit and place into casserole dish.
Trim edges from light bread and cut each slice into 4 strips.
Place lattice fashion over fruit.
Mix sugar, margarine and egg.
Pour over fruit and bread slices.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato bonbons
directions: Mash sweet potatoes until light and fluffy.
Beat in butter, sugar, salt and orange rind; let cool.
Divide into 12 portions. Press potatoes around each marshmallow half, being careful to keep marshmallow in center.
Shape into ovals.
Coat each with melted butter.
Roll in crushed cornflakes.
Top with pecan.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mix and pour in sprayed muffin pans.
Bake at 450° for 6 minutes and at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: grape nut salad
directions: Mix and let set 45 minutes before serving.

title: sloppy burgers
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in skillet until brown.
Remove from heat and drain fat.
Return to heat and add barbecue sauce. Simmer about 15 minutes. Serve on hamburger buns.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: deviled crab
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Fold in crabmeat.
Put into greased casserole dish.
Top with dabs of butter and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: salmon burgers
directions: Drain salmon and flake, reserving 2 tablespoons liquid. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Add balance of ingredients.
Mix. Form into patties.
Chill.
Fry in oil until lightly browned.
Top with Ranch dressing.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Very good.

title: peg's dip
directions: Spread cream cheese into a 9-inch pie plate.
Cover with chili. Top with cheese and microwave until cheese is melted.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: canadian bacon-cheese pockets
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
On lightly floured surface, roll each biscuit into 4-inch circle. Prick half the circles with fork. Divide bacon, cheese and mustard evenly among 5 circles, leaving a 1/2-inch border.
Trim cheese to fit.
Top with remaining biscuit rounds.
Press edges with fork to seal. Brush top with egg yolk. Bake 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add butter, eggs and vanilla and mix well; pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: honey pecans
directions: Combine
sugar,
water
and
honey
in a heavy saucepan, stirring to
mix.
Bring
mixture
to a boil (do not stir), and cook to
soft ball stage (240°).
Remove from heat; add flavorings, and cook to lukewarm.
Beat with an electric mixer 2 to 3 minutes
or
until
mixture turns creamy.
Add pecans, stirring until
coated.
Drop
by heaping teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Let cool.
Yields 3 1/4 cups.

title: gingham carrots
directions: Pare and coarsely grate carrots (about 2 to 2 1/2 cups). Place in saucepan with butter, instant onion and water.
Cover and cook gently until carrots are tender, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in brown sugar, nutmeg and salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: easy oven breaded chicken
directions: Pour enough salad dressing over chicken to coat each piece. Marinate for a couple of hours.
Dip each piece in bread crumbs, coating each piece on both sides.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: sand-kaker(sand cookies)
directions: Press into sand cake forms, spreading dough as thin as possible.
Bake at 300° until a very light brown, about 25 minutes.
Cool and remove from forms.

title: caramel pie
directions: Take the labels off of Eagle brand cream cans and boil in large pot of water for 2-3 hours.
When finished open cans and pour into pie shell.
Chill pie in freezer for 30 minutes; then top with Cool Whip.
Scatter mini- chocolate chips over Cool Whip. Store in freezer.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Blend dry ingredients together.
Add milk and cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks and cook one minute longer.
Add vanilla.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice and stirring in half of coconut.
Sprinkle half of remaining coconut in baked pie shell.
Pour filling into crust.
Beat egg whites with 4 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon tartar.
Sprinkle remaining coconut over top and brown slightly.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine eggs and 1/4 cup of the tomato soup.
Stir in uncooked rice, bread crumbs, onion, parsley, salt and pepper. Add beef and mix well.
Shape meat mixture into 25 small balls (about the size of ping pong ball or golf ball). Place in 10-inch skillet.
Mix remaining soup with Worcestershire sauce and 1/2 cup water.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer (covered) for 30 to 35 minutes, stirring gently twice during cooking.
Serve over hot cooked egg noodles (and with tossed salad).
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle rice over bottom of pan. Heat soups and milk until well blended and pour over rice.
Put pieces of chicken over rice and sprinkle dry onion soup mix over chicken.
Seal with foil and bake 2 hours at 325° to 350°.

title: chili
directions: Brown the ground beef; add onions to meat and cook a little longer.
Drain meat and pour into large pot.
Add all remaining ingredients (except Velveeta) and cook for about 20 minutes. Serve and top with chunks of Velveeta.

title: chili sauce or salsa
directions: Loosen tomato skins by scalding or steaming; peel.
Finely chop the vegetables or put through coarse blade of chopper.
Put chopped tomatoes and vegetables into a large kettle.
Tie spices in clean cheesecloth bag and add to tomato/vegetable mixture.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove spice bag.
Add salt, sugar and vinegar.
For chili sauce, boil rapidly for 5 minutes.
Makes about 5 pints.
For salsa, allow to cook additional time to desired consistency.

title: extra-easy lasagna
directions: In 10-inch skillet, cook beef until browned.
Stir often to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Heat through.
Stir often.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Mix cream cheese with other ingredients.
Spread 2 tablespoons on tortilla.
Roll up and cut into 6 to 8 pieces.
Makes 60 to 80 pinwheels.
(Dip into salsa before eating.)

title: banana bread
directions: Mash ripe bananas with fork.
Stir in other ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour in preheated 325° oven.
Pour into well-greased and floured pan.

title: tomato bread
directions: Peel and cut up tomatoes into large pieces.
Break up bread as for filling.
Mix and put into hot greased pan.
Stir and cook until well blended and hot.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in order.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Blend butter, 1 cup sugar, eggs, vanilla and milk.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, nuts and grated lemon rind.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Mix lemon juice and 1/3 cup sugar; pour over top of hot loaf.

title: pecan pie]
directions: Line the pie shell with chopped pecans.
Combine the sugar, corn syrup, flour, vanilla and salt; mix until blended.
Beat in the eggs, one at a time, mixing well each time.
Pour into the nut-lined pie shell; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until firm, about 1 hour.

title: crab cakes
directions: Cook onion, green pepper and celery in 1/2 stick margarine. Beat eggs with mayonnaise, mustard, bread and parsley.
Season with Old Bay seasoning.
Combine all ingredients with only a dash of cayenne pepper.
Fry in margarine with 2 tablespoons of cooking oil added to prevent margarine from browning.

title: no cook lye soap
directions: Mix lye in water.
Mix Borax in a little extra water.
Add ammonia and mix with grease.
Stir well.
Strain.
Pour in glass pan and set aside to harden and mark in bars.

title: dannon muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Stir in yogurt and milk until moistened.
Fill muffin cup 3/4 full.
Bake 18 minutes until brown at 400°.
Makes 12.

title: chicken breasts deluxe
directions: Arrange chicken in a 2-quart buttered baking dish.
Combine soups and sherry.
Stir in cheese, mushrooms, sour cream and green onions.
Pour over chicken breasts.
Bake uncovered at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water with 1 teaspoon sugar. Heat 1 1/2 cups water, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and shortening until dissolved; then cool to lukewarm.
In a large mixing bowl beat eggs well.
Add shortening, sugar, salt and water mixture.
Beat well. Add dissolved yeast.
Add about 5 cups flour; mix well.
Then add 2 to 3 cups more or less.
Turn on a floured board and knead.
Return to mixing bowl in which a little oil has been added.
Flip over so top will be moistened with oil.
Let rise to double in size.
Knead again.
Make into rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake in a 400° oven until golden brown.
While hot, brush with butter.
May be reheated in microwave or frozen.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until nearly done. Drain (don't overcook).
Cook bacon and onion until crispy.
Don't drain grease.
Add the vinegar, sugar and water. Bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Pour over potatoes. Cover with cheese.

title: baked onions
directions: Wash and clean onions; slit 4 times in top 1/4 to 1/8-inch thick.
Add other ingredients and cook until tender in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hack's five hour stew
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 3-quart covered casserole dish for 5 hours at 275°.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased 9 inch square baking pan, bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes or until center springs back when touched.

title: brisket with cranberry sauce
directions: Combine oil and garlic; rub evenly over cut surfaces of frozen meat.
Stand rib, bone side down, in a shallow baking pan between potatoes placed like book ends.

title: banana pudding
directions: Heat milk over medium fire until it steams.
Mix flour and sugar in bowl.
Stir in eggs.
Add some milk to mixture to make creamy.
Pour it into milk and cook until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.
Allow to cool.
Layer cookies and bananas.
Pour pudding.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: hot ham and cheese sandwich
directions: Grind the green tomatoes.
Drain juice.
Measure juice and throw away.
Add the same amount of water to pulp.
Bring tomatoes to a boil.
Drain again and add same amount of water to pulp. Bring to a boil.
Repeat this process one more time.
Drain.

title: no oil 3 bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill overnight.
Just before serving, drain and toss lightly.
Serves 10.

title: cheese balls
directions: Combine cheeses
in
a bowl, adding garlic and Tabasco, blending until well
mixed.
Chill	2 to 3 hours.
Form into a ball, rolling the
ball
in
the nuts and then in the parsley. Chill.
Remove from refrigerator 30 minutes before serving.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix
hash
brown
potatoes,
sour cream, grated cheese, onion, soup and salt all together.
Melt 1 stick margarine in 9
x 13-inch
pan.
Put	potato mixture in pan.	Crumble soda crackers. Melt
other
stick of margarine and mix with crackers.
Put on top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: hot chipped beef dip
directions: Mix well and bake for 20 minutes at 350°
(can do everything in the same casserole dish).
Let stand 10 minutes, then serve with Triscuits and crackers.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla. Stir in dry ingredients; mix well.
Chill dough.
Roll out quite thin; cut into shapes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes, until light golden brown.
Decorate with frosting, jimmies, sugar or whatever you desire.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil together the water, cornstarch and sugar.
Add jello and cool.
Add strawberries and salt.
Put in baked pie shell.

title: hot cross buns
directions: Mix together butter, scalded milk, 3 tablespoons sugar and 1 yeast.
Add eggs, sugar, flour, salt, cinnamon and raisins.
Mix together to form soft dough.
Cover, let rise until doubled.
Punch down.
Divide dough and make about 24 rolls, depending on size. Cover and let rise about 1 hour.
Make cross with sharp knife. Bake in 400° oven about 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with crosses.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix ingredients together; form into ball.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Roll in chopped parsley.
Center on plate surrounded by Ritz crackers.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin first with mixer.
Mix flour, sugar and spice together.
Add this to the pumpkin, beating after.	Beat eggs before you add them to the mixture.
Add milk and mix well. Double this and it will make 3 pies.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake 15 minutes on 400°, then for 30 to 35 minutes on 350°.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: In pan, brown meat and drain.
Add onion, rice, 1/2 can tomato sauce and 1/2 cup water.
Add spices and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Fill peppers (cut tops, deseed and wash).
Pour remaining tomato sauce over peppers.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until done.
Can also be cooked in crock-pot after filling is put into peppers.

title: russian tea
directions: Put all ingredients in large container with tight lid.
Shake well until blended.
Do not use blender.
Use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls for each cup of boiling water.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large mixing bowl, beat condensed milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Add Bisquick mix and vanilla.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
(Do not overbake.)
Cool.
Store tightly covered at room temperature.

title: betty's breakfast whirls
directions: Mix Bisquick, oleo and milk; refrigerate 1 hour.
Mix sausages and cheese and let stand at room temperature for about 10 minutes. Divide dough in half; roll each piece to a large rectangle about 1/4-inch thick.
Spread half of meat mixture and completely over each piece and roll as for jelly roll.
Wrap in plastic wrap and freeze for 1 hour.
Remove from freezer and slice 1/3-inch thick. Do not thaw; bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Will keep in freezer for about 30 days.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients and mix well.
Add pecans.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add last. Pour into prepared loaf pans.
Bake at 325° until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: bran muffin batter
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cereal with buttermilk and let sit in large bowl for 10 minutes.
Add all other ingredients and mix by hand until blended.
Add fruits or nuts to batter.
Use paper liners in muffin pan or grease and flour 1 bread pan.
Bake muffins for 18 to 20 minutes and bread for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: puff pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place a skillet or cake pan with 2 tablespoons of margarine in oven until sizzling.
Pour batter into sizzling pan and bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes. Serve with syrup or strawberries or any kind of pie filling.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add beaten eggs, salt, vanilla and lemon juice.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° the first 10 minutes and then at 350° until done.

title: chocolate knockout brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, 1/2 cup milk, butter and water.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes in 350° oven.
While the cake is cooking, melt caramels with 1/4 to 1/2 cup evaporated milk.
Pour over partially cooked cake.
Add chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour rest of cake mix over filling.
Bake additional 16 to 18 minutes or until done.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Mix brown sugar, mustard and cornstarch.
Add water, vinegar and raisins.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick.
Add butter and blend well.
Makes 2 cups.
Serve with ham.

title: e-z peanut butter pie
directions: Cream peanut butter and sugar.
Add Cool Whip and cream well. Pour into crust; cover and put in freezer.

title: grandmom's corn casserole
directions: In bowl, mix flour, baking powder and sugar.
Add egg, oil and milk.
Mix well.
Add corn.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on.
Bake at 350° until browned in greased casserole dish.

title: apricot dip
directions: Cream the first three ingredients together.
Add preserves and pecans or walnuts.
Mix well.

title: bonbons
directions: Put sugar, coconut, milk and nuts in bowl.
Mix good and pour melted oleo over all.
Work with hands until mixed real good. Roll in small balls.

title: easy bean dip
directions: Layer in order in a baking dish and bake at 350° until cheese is melted and bubbling.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugars, shortening, peanut butter and egg.
Mix well, then blend in flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Roll into balls and flatten with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° until golden.

title: lime sherbet
directions: Add sugar, lemon juice and rind to dissolved Jell-O.
Add milk.
Place in 2 refrigerator trays.
Freeze, then beat and return to trays; freeze again.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt margarine. Mix with pretzels, pecans and sugar. Put into bottom of 9x13 inch baking dish. Bake at 350 degrees 8 minutes. Cool.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Grate cabbage.
Clean celery and slice thinly into crescents. Cut apple into quarters; core, but do not peel and cut in small pieces.
Add dressing as desired.

title: homemade fudgesicles
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Stir over medium heat and boil 1 minute.
Pour into ice cube trays or Dixie cups. Freeze.
Will fill 2 sets of ice cube trays.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix together and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 425°, then turn down to 300° and bake until brown.

title: relish
directions: Clean the mangoes, onions and celery and grind together in grinder.
Cover with boiling water.
Let stand for 15 minutes. Drain and get all water out.

title: easy no fail pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour onto hot griddle. Don't beat batter.
Use all of the batter up as if it stands, it goes flat.
Good to use in making waffles.

title: mary's peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine milk, water and sugar in 3-quart saucepan.
Place over medium heat and bring to a boil.
