Boil for about 20 minutes or until a small amount forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water. Remove from heat.
Add butter, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat all together and continue beating by hand until fudge starts to thicken.
Pour into lightly greased pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the butter, granulated sugar and powdered sugar.
Add eggs and salt.
Add oil and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, soda and cream of tartar; add to mixture.
Press with cookie shooter, or roll into balls and press with bottom of glass. Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with colored sugar. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Begin the day before you want these.
Trim crusts from each slice of bread and cut each slice into three sticks.
Put sticks on large cookie sheets and put into a very slow oven about 225°.
Do not brown, just dry them out.
Turn off oven and let bread remain in oven overnight.
The next day, melt peanut butter and oil in a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Stir often and do not let it stick.
When hot and smoothly blended remove from heat and dip the dry bread sticks, coating all 4 sides and ends.
Carefully roll each stick in crushed corn flakes and lay them on cake rack to dry.
Good for diabetics.

title: broccoli orange salad
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a bowl; set aside.
Combine low-fat mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar, add to broccoli mixture. Stir gently to coat.
Carefully stir in mandarin oranges.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight before serving.
(It can be served immediately, but it's better after some refrigeration.)

title: fruity fruit
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Top with nuts and serve.
Serves 6.

title: health wise baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash and pat dry chicken.
Combine crackers, milk and seasonings.
Place in a sealable plastic bag. Pour margarine on a small plate.
Coat chicken in margarine and place in bag with dry mix.
Shake to coat.
Place in a baking pan sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle on some leftover crumbs.
Drizzle remaining butter over chicken.
Bake about 20 minutes.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, melt butter; layer in order graham cracker crumbs, coconut, chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Pour over all one can of condensed milk; top with chopped nuts.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned in 350° oven.

title: strawberry cake and filling
directions: Mix cake mix, jello and flour.
Add water and oil.
Beat well. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and strawberries.
Bake in layers for 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: shrimp spread
directions: In a small bowl beat cream cheese, sour cream and mayonnaise until smooth.
Spread on a 12-inch round platter.
Cover with seafood sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese, shrimp and onions.
Cover and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown the meat in large skillet and drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, onions and garlic salt.
Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles according to package directions. Drain and layer bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Following the noodles, layer half the cottage cheese, Mozzarella and meat sauce.
Repeat the layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes and then let stand for 10 minutes.

title: easy garden vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease pie plate.
Mix broccoli, onion, green pepper and cheese in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour over top of first mixture.
Bake until golden brown, 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before cutting.

title: holiday salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple together.
Add Cool Whip.
Blend together and then add marshmallows and nuts.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.

title: lemon bars
directions: Make a dough with first 3 ingredients.
Pat this dough into a Teflon cookie sheet with sides.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put in and cook for 15 minutes.

title: chicken westmoreland
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: date nut balls
directions: Bring sugar, margarine, egg and dates to rolling boil.
Cook 2 more minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and mix well.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts; mix well.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoonful in coconut.
Form into balls and roll in coconut.

title: sweet potato custards
directions: Mix and pour into pans.
Cook at 250° until done.

title: strawberry jubilee
directions: Preheat oven to 325° to 350°. Lightly grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan (set aside). Coarsely chop 1/2 cup of nuts (set aside). Finely chop remaining nuts; set aside.

title: pepper cabbage
directions: Finely chop cabbage and pepper.
Grate onion and carrot.
Add to cabbage and pepper.
Blend next 4 ingredients and pour over cabbage mixture.
Mix well.

title: icing for yummy strawberry cake
directions: Blend strawberries into sugar and butter.
Mix until reaches right consistency.

title: jellied spinach salad
directions: Dissolve lemon gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 2 1/2 cups cold water.
As gelatin sets, stir in mayonnaise.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into dish and chill.

title: snowy mashed potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook potatoes until tender. Drain and beat with electric mixer. Add cream cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper, garlic salt and chives.
Beat until light.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole. Sprinkle with paprika and dot with butter. Bake for 30 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: five bean salad
directions: Drain liquid from 5 cans of beans. Drain and rinse kidney beans. Combine first 7 ingredients in large bowl. Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well. Pour over vegetables, tossing gently. Cover and refrigerate 8 to 10 hours before serving.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Mix cranberries with sugar and let stand 15 minutes. After jello cools, add all other ingredients and place in refrigerator.
Serve when firm.

title: texas cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Bring oleo, cocoa and water to a boil. Pour hot mixture over flour and sugar.
Beat.
Add eggs, sour cream, soda and vanilla.
Beat well.
Bake in a cookie sheet (11 x 16-inches) for 20 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: tangy mustard chutney
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.
Brush on chicken or pork to grill.

title: turkey cashew casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Reserve 1/2 cup noodles.
Place remaining noodles in mixing bowl.
Add turkey, celery, nuts and scallions; toss lightly.
In small bowl blend soup, broth and soy sauce.
Pour over turkey mixture; mix well.
Turn into casserole; sprinkle with reserved mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: baked potato skins
directions: Slice potatoes lengthwise. Scoop out 3/4 of the potatoes (use in another recipe).
Set skins on cookie sheet and place in oven 4-inches away from top element. Broil 8 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheeses.
Season well and add bacon and paprika. Broil another 4 to 5 minutes. Serve hot with sour cream.

title: crock-pot spaghetti sauce
directions: *Can use fresh chopped tomatoes, stewed tomatoes or any variation.
I've even used V-8!

title: minerva's arroz con pollo
directions: Cut chicken into smaller pieces.
Cook halfway in oil in hot frying pan.
In another frying pan with cover, brown rice in 1 tablespoon oil.
Transfer chicken to rice pan and cook a couple of minutes.
Chop white onion, tomatoes and bell pepper and add to chicken and rice mixture in medium hot pan.
Continue cooking. Grind spices in Mexican molcajete or mortar and pestle until pasty. Add small amount of water, then add to chicken and rice.
Mix. Add enough water to cover rice and chicken; salt and pepper to taste. Add tomato sauce.
Top with cilantro.
Cover and cook until water recedes fully.
Enjoy my Grandmother's recipe.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix ingredients with mixer and put in pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts, if desired.
Keep chilled.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into a casserole dish.
Top with topping. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: festive party punch
directions: In large bowl, scoop sherbet with rounded ice cream scoop. Empty the frozen lemonade and limeade by spoonfuls.
Add Vernors and ice.
Stir.

title: spinach and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook both vegetables and drain well.
Mix together.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz.
Put in flat casserole.
Peel tomatoes; cut in small pieces and place on top of vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: perfectly easy dinner rolls
directions: Combine water and yeast. Let stand until yeast is foamy, about 5 minutes. Stir in butter, sugar, eggs and salt. Beat in flour, 1 cup at a time, until dough is too stiff to mix. (May not need all flour.) Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: rocky road bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Heat 1/2 cup of the chocolate chips and then margarine in heavy 1-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring occasionally, until melted.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add the rest of the ingredients.
Pat into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt 6 ounces chocolate chips and 2/3 cup peanut butter.
Put on top of mixture when you take it out of the oven.

title: patsy's indiana sugar cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Frost if desired.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 13 dozen.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Combine everything but wing flings. In electric skillet at 275°, lay wing flings and add mixture. Turn when boiling.
Cook 20 minutes with lid, turning occasionally. Remove lid and cook until caramelized (approximately 20 minutes).

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cream potatoes and 1/2 stick margarine until melted.
Add salt, sugar, eggs, milk, vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour into greased casserole dish (13 x 9-inch).
Top with mixture of the brown sugar, flour, 1/2 stick margarine and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream together eggs, shortening, sugars and vanilla.
Add other ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased baking sheet. Bake at 350°.

title: fruit squares
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla. Add flour, a little at a time.
Spread 3/4 of batter with spatula into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread filling over batter.
Drop remaining batter by teaspoon on top of filling.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cooked salad dressing
directions: Bring all ingredients, except mayonnaise, to a boil.
Cool and add mayonnaise.
(This is good for potato salad, macaroni salad or deviled eggs.)

title: red stew for polenta(umido)
directions: Brown meats and onion in oil and butter.
Add remaining ingredients and stew until meats are tender.
Add 1 can drained peas, any spices you like and tomato sauce (all optional).
Serve over polenta.

title: apples in amaretto sauce
directions: Slice apple thin and arrange in medium size baking dish.
Melt butter in microwave.
Add sugar and Amaretto.
Drizzle over apples.
Sprinkle apples with cinnamon, raisins or pecans, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Spoon sauce over apples and bake additional 10 minutes, until tender.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: With a fork, prick bottom of pastry shell.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and set aside.
Reduce heat to 350°.
While pastry shell is baking, cut 6 slices of the cheese and set aside.

title: homestyle barbecue sauce
directions: Whisk all ingredients together until smooth.
Brush on meats, turning frequently, during last 20 minutes of cooking.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Great on chicken or pork.

title: sunshine spinach salad(heart healthy)
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Chill until serving time.
Toss dressing with salad ingredients.

title: aunt nora's fig preserves
directions: Add all ingredients and cook 20 to 25 minutes. Boil and stir. Seal while hot.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well. Sift together the flour, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon and add to the first mixture.
Add the nuts and apples.
Mix.
Bake in a 9-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: butterfinger cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add egg whites and beat well. Blend in peanut butter and vanilla.
Combine in small bowl the flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well. Stir in chopped candy bars.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls and bake at 350° for 10 - 12 min.
Serves 8 - 10.

title: roast crock-pot venison
directions: Season roast with salt.
Roll in flour and brown in hot bacon drippings.
Place in crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients,
cover and
cook on high for 2 hours.
Then turn to low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: date nut bread #2
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a bowl.
When cool, add sugar, egg and flour.
Mix well.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan greased and lined with brown paper.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: easy chicken mushroom bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Arrange chicken pieces in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In
a
medium bowl, combine remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour over chicken. Bake at 375° for about 1 hour until tender.
Serve mushroom mixture as gravy.

title: dr. pepper baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except bacon. Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Cut bacon in 2-inch strips and arrange on top.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexicali pudding
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine pudding mix, coffee granules and cinnamon.
Slowly stir in milk.
Bring to full boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Pour pudding into 4 serving dishes; cover and refrigerate.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Slice sausage; brown in oil.
Add onion, garlic, carrots and basil.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add zucchini, tomatoes, bouillon and cabbage.
Bring to boil, then simmer for 1 hour.
Add beans and cook 20 minutes longer.

title: chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix brown sugar, dry mustard and garlic powder in a large bowl with a lid or a plastic bag.
Place 4 or 5 wings in the bowl or bag until coated.
After coating all wings, place in a large roasting pan.
Mix soy sauce with corn syrup and pour over wings.
Place in oven.
Cook 1 3/4 to 2 hours.
Baste every 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn once in an hour.

title: honey corn muffins
directions: Sift flour once, measure, add baking powder and salt.
Sift again; add cornmeal.
Wash, pare and dice apples.
Combine egg, milk, honey and shortening.
Add all at once to flour-cornmeal mixture, stirring only enough to dampen all flour.
Fold in apple. Bake in well greased 2-inch muffin pans at 400° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Empty package of broccoli in large bowl.
Cook, covered, in microwave on High 5 to 7 minutes; drain.
Add soup, onion, cheese and egg.
Mix all.
Microwave, covered, on Medium-high for 15 to 18 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: russian tea (instant)
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Place 2 rounded tablespoons of mix in each cup.
Fill with boiling water and stir well.
Dry mix can be kept covered in storage container. Makes 32 servings.
(I usually use 2 heaping teaspoons per cup; it depends on how strong you like your tea.)

title: dump cake
directions: Grease pan (9 x 13-inch). Pour in pineapple.
Top with pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix over top.
Add nuts.
Cut margarine in small slices.
Spread over top (do not stir).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Good served hot or cold.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and syrup.
Stir in pecans (I use enough to take up mixture).
Add vanilla and butter.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake until firm at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugars, beating well.
Add egg.
Add oil and vanilla.
Mix flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oatmeal and remaining ingredients.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten each ball with tines of fork.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool slightly. Remove from cookie sheet and cool.
Yield:
10 dozen.

title: michele's rich fudge(makes about 9 to 10 dozen pieces)
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, combine sugar, butter and evaporated milk.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture comes to a full boil, 10 to 14 minutes.
Reduce heat to medium.
Boil, stirring constantly, until candy thermometer reaches 228° or until small amount of mixture dropped into ice water forms a 2-inch soft thread, 6 to 7 minutes.

title: holiday poke cake
directions: Place cake layers, top sides up, in 2 clean 9-inch round cake pans.

Pierce cake with large fork at 1/2-inch intervals. Dissolve each flavor of gelatin completely in 1 cup boiling water in separate bowls. Carefully pour red gelatin over 1 cake layer and lime gelatin over the second cake layer.
Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: never fail caramel frosting
directions: Mix and bring to a boil.
Thicken with powdered sugar, then spread upon cake.

title: dirt pie
directions: Beat pudding mix with milk in bowl until thick.
Stir in other ingredients.
Mix well with mixer at low speed.
Layer 1/2 crumbled Oreos in pan.
Cover with pudding mixture.
Top with rest of Oreo crumbs.
Put in freezer.

title: french onion soup(the secret is lots of onions and gruyere cheese.)
directions: Thinly slice onions lengthwise (julienne).
Saute in heavy pot with 2 tablespoons butter and the olive oil until limp.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes more.
Add broth and simmer 30 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Dry toast 8 to 10 1/2-inch slices of French bread about 1/2 hour at 275°.
Grate 1/2 cup Gruyere cheese and mix with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Dice enough Gruyere cheese to make 3/4 cup of 1/2-inch cubes.
Ladle hot soup (if cold heat the bowls in oven 15 to 20 minutes at 350°) into 6 to 7 bowls.
Divide Gruyere cubes evenly into bowls.
Add 1 + tablespoon Port wine to each bowl.
Cover with toasted French bread.
Sprinkle grated cheese mixture on toast.
Dribble each with butter.
Bake 10 minutes in oven at 425°.

title: cockeyed cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in a 9 x 9-inch greased cake pan.
Make 3 holes in dry mixture.
Pour oil in one hole, vinegar in one hole and vanilla in one hole.
Pour water over the top. Beat with spoon until nearly smooth and flour is stirred in.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot dish roll-up
directions: Unroll crescent rolls to form a long rectangle on an ungreased cookie sheet; pinch perforations together.
Add soup, pepper and onion to beef.
Place mixture down the middle of pastry.
Pull up edges to form a rim.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until light brown.
Place cheese on top and bake an additional 5 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes and mix all ingredients, except crackers.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix Ritz crackers and 1 cup butter together.
Spread over potato mixture and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: green goddess dressing(low calorie)
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend at medium speed until smooth.
Makes approximately 2 cups.
There are 16 calories per tablespoon.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Put 1/2 dried beef in bottom of casserole dish.
Then place chicken wrapped in bacon over that.
Mix sour cream and cream of mushroom soup together.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle dried beef over top.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 350° uncovered.

title: jemima's jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients except jam and egg whites.
Blend and then add jam.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Frosting is optional, but a Caramel Icing or Cream Cheese Icing is delicious on this cake.

title: sunset jam
directions: Wash, peel and core pears.
Chop very fine or crush.
Place in preserving kettle.
Add drained pineapple, chopped cherries, the sugar and the lemon juice.
Mix well.

title: hot sauce
directions: Blend all together for 2 seconds in blender.

title: brown sugar squares
directions: Mix brown sugar, oleo (or oil), warm coffee and vanilla.
Cool and add eggs.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Spread on jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: rouladen
directions: Take Rouladen; lay flat, salt and pepper to taste. Add your strip of bacon in the center from top to bottom. Lay pickles in middle. Cover with onions.

title: hamburger pot pie
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add Veg-All, potato soup and milk.
Put bottom crust in pie plate.
Add mixture.
Top with pie crust. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and drain.
Combine tomato sauce, tomato
paste and spices together in pot.	Add drained meat. Bring
to
a
boil	and
then simmer on low heat for 20 minutes, covered.
Stir
occasionally
and
may
add
a small amount
of water as needed.
Boil noodles according to package directions. Drain noodles.
Grease oblong pan.	Layer according
to
this: noodles
(may
slightly
overlap), meat sauce, sliced
Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese and grated Parmesan cheese.	Repeat	layers once.
Bake
20 to 30 minutes, uncovered,	at
or until cheese looks melted.
Allow to stand about 10 minutes before serving.

title: london tea cakes
directions: Mix salt, baking powder and flour.
Mix and add butter or margarine, sugar and enough milk to form soft dough.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Spread lightly with butter.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Roll up and cut in slices.
Place in pan.
Sprinkle with sugar again.
Add a spoonful of jam to each slice and bake at 400°.
Serve with afternoon tea.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt margarine on low heat.
Add milk.
Add firmly packed light brown sugar and stir until melted.
Blend and bring to a boil.
Let boil for 1 minute.
Cool and add confectioners sugar, enough to spread easily.
May be used on any cake.

title: welsh dessert cakes
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder into a large bowl. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Mix in raisins, walnuts and nutmeg.
Stir in eggs and vanilla until well blended (mixture will be dry).
Turn out onto a lightly floured board and pat to a 1/4-inch thickness.
With a floured cutter, cut into 2-inch rounds.

title: punch bowl salad(serves approximately 20)
directions: Layer as follows:
lettuce, cauliflower, red onion with sugar and bacon.
Spread salad dressing on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Toss when ready to serve.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix instant vanilla pudding according to directions on package.
Fold in Cool Whip and sour cream, mixing well.
Place vanilla wafers in dish, then slice bananas.
Now, alternate with a mixture of sour cream and pudding mix, according to depth of dish. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Top with Cool Whip.
This makes two nice sized dishes.

title: freezer dumplings
directions: Melt margarine; cool, then add milk to margarine, then add egg and milk mixture to flour.
Mix together.
Make 3 balls.
Cool in icebox for 10 minutes.
Roll on floured board until thin.
Cut into strips and small pieces.
Place on cookie sheets that are covered with wax paper.
Freeze.
Next day, place in Ziploc freezer bags.

title: great cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Whip milk and cream cheese until creamy.
Fold in Cool Whip and sugar.
Pour into crust.
Add cherry pie filling.
Chill.

title: superb baked chicken
directions: Mix together crackers and cheese.
Melt margarine in separate container.
Mix together soup, water, sour cream, and mushrooms; set aside.
Dip chicken into margarine and roll in crackers and cheese mixture.
Place chicken in shallow baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Pour soup, water, sour cream and mushrooms over chicken. Use remaining cracker crumbs, mixed with remaining margarine, as a topping for chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crunchie bits
directions: Mix all the cereal together.
Melt almond bark and mix with cereal.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: microwave french onion soup
directions: Microwave onions in butter on High, covered, for 9 to 11 minutes or until transparent.
Add water, bouillon (or broth) and spices.
Cook on High, covered, 8 to 10 minutes.
Top with cheese and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Soften cream cheese, then cream in sugar with mixer. Fold in whipped cream. Pour into crust. Add cherries on top.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese set until at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients well.
Let set 24 hours in refrigerator.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Blend together flour, shortening, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt
until crumbly.
Mix together the dry yeast and warm water until dissolved.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Add to flour mixture.
Add buttermilk; mix well.
Roll or pat out on floured surface to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter or small glass.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.
Dough may be refrigerated until needed up to 2 weeks.

title: beets with brown sugar and pineapple
directions: Combine brown sugar, cornstarch and salt in a saucepan with pineapple chunks and juice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until the sauce thickens and comes to a boil.
Add margarine, lemon juice and beets.
Continue to cook for 5 minutes more or until beets are heated through.
Serves 5.

title: 9 day slaw
directions: Stir together cabbage, onions, green pepper and sugar.
Bring to a boil the salad oil, vinegar, celery seed, salt and 2 cups of sugar.
Immediately pour this hot mixture over the cabbage mixture.
Chill overnight before serving.
Keep stored in refrigerator.

title: egg breakfast casserole
directions: Layer bread, cheese and sausages in a buttered casserole dish. First and last layer is bread.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses, then blend all ingredients except pecans. Chill.
Shape into one large ball or two small ones.
Roll in pecans.
Serve with a variety of crackers.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Saute cabbage and onion in margarine.
Add 1 tablespoon flour and cook for 1 minute.
Add chicken broth, lemon juice, sugar and tomatoes.
Simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cook sugar and syrup until mixture thickens.
Beat eggs. Slowly add hot mixture to eggs, beating constantly.
Add butter, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in hot oven 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 30 minutes. Cool and serve with or without whipped cream.

title: easy roast
directions: In a Dutch oven over medium heat in salad oil, brown a roast on all sides.
Pour off the fat.
Empty soup mix on the meat. Stir in mushroom soup, 1/4 cup water and bay leaf (remove before serving).
Cover.
Simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours until tender.
Add more water as necessary during cooking.
Remove beef to platter.
Add flour or cornstarch to 1/4 cup water.
Stir until smooth.
Stir into pan drippings over high heat, stirring constantly.
Cut meat into thin slices.
Serve meat and gravy together.

title: lazy day grasshopper pie
directions: Line bottom of 9-inch pie plate with chocolate wafer cookies, filling in spaces with pieces.
Line sides with 1/2 cookies.
In bowl, combine marshmallow cream, milk, peppermint extract and food coloring.
Whip until fluffy.
Fold in whipped cream.
Fill cookie crust and freeze 8 hours or overnight.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chameleon parfait
directions: Select pudding flavors to compliment fruit and cake. Examples:
vanilla pudding with peaches or berries, banana pudding with bananas or coconut, chocolate pudding with chocolate cake or chips.
Alternate two pudding flavors in each parfait for appearance and additional flavor.
Prepare each pudding just before adding to parfait; they set up fast!

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in small bowl.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake 30 minutes at 350° topped with buttered bread crumbs.

title: peppered tenderloin
directions: Purchase tenderloin trimmed, rolled and tied.
The night before, poke holes in tenderloin throughout entire piece with a fork.
Rub in teriyaki sauce, garlic salt and ground pepper.
Wrap in foil.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Take out 1 hour before time to serve.
Unwrap foil; roll tenderloin in any juice on foil. Cook at 450° for 40 to 60 minutes (rare to well done).
Test with thermometer.
Slice; serve warm or chilled.

title: hot chicken dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a crock-pot. Heat on low for a couple of hours. Serve with crackers.

title: aunt jean's easy pecan pie
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients together and stir in pecans. Bake in 3 shallow or 2 deep dish pie shells at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°.
Grease and flour two loaf pans. Beat eggs, then add oil, sugar, grated zucchini and vanilla.
Cream together.
Sift and measure 3 cups flour.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients to other mixture which has been creamed.
Mix all thoroughly.
Add broken nut meats last.
Blend and pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, two at a time, mixing well.
Add flour, sifting and mixing well.
Add drained pineapple.
Pour batter into tube pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: egg strada(great for a brunch or lunch)
directions: Butter bread slices on one side.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, arrange bread in a layer and cover with half of the cheese.
Cut sausages into bite size pieces and spread over cheese.
Make a second layer of buttered bread slices and top with remaining cheese.
In blender, beat eggs, milk and mustard.
Pour egg mixture over bread and cheese.
Dust with paprika.
Let stand, covered, in refrigerator overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Additional cheese may be added according to taste.
Serves 8.

title: no peek beef stew
directions: Mix all together and bake at 250° for 4 hours.
Do not open lid while cooking.

title: old fashion bean with ham soup
directions: In a large soup pot, combine beans and 2 1/2 quarts of water. Bring to a boil; cover and continue to boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and allow pot to stand, covered, 1 hour.
Add ham hocks, onion, garlic and bay leaf.
Cover; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 hours.
Add potatoes, celery, carrot and parsley. Cover and continue simmering, at least 1 hour or all day if you wish.
Remove bay leaf and meat.
Dice meat and return to pot. Season with salt and pepper.

title: christy cake
directions: Mix 1 box of cake mix as directed on box. Cook in round pans, greased. Makes 3 layers after cake has cooled.

title: hungarian goulash with sauerkraut
directions: Cut beef into 1 1/2-inch chunks.
Peel and slice onions.
In a Dutch oven, heat salad oil over high heat.
Add beef chunks in a single layer (do not overcrowd) and saute over medium heat. Continue cooking, turning to brown on all sides.
Using tongs, remove beef to a bowl as it browns.
Continue browning rest of beef.
This will take 20 to 30 minutes in all.
Add onions to drippings; cook, stirring, until tender and golden, about 10 minutes.
Return beef to Dutch oven.
Add paprika, salt and pepper, stirring until well combined.
Stir in 3/4 cup beef broth.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, covered, 2 hours, or until the beef chunks are fork-tender.
While beef cooks, prepare sauerkraut.
In colander, drain sauerkraut well.
Pare potato; grate enough potato to measure 3/4 cup.
In hot oleo in large skillet, saute chopped onion (1/2 cup) until golden brown, about 3 minutes.
Add sauerkraut, potato, caraway
seed, brown sugar and 2 cups boiling water.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, 20 minutes, or until most of the liquid has evaporated.

title: salmon ball
directions: Drain salmon.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly and chill.
Make into ball and roll in chopped nuts.

title: labor day chili
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Stir in tomato sauce and dry ingredients that have been combined.
Stir well.
Let simmer, stirring frequently for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Stew chicken in about 1 1/2-quarts water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Chicken is done when tender and pulling away from bone. Take chicken out of water it was cooked in and set aside to cool. When chicken is cool enough to touch, remove from bones.
In the water chicken was cooked in, add chicken broth or cream of chicken soup and margarine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes.

title: "clean" chicken nachos
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In bowl, combine shredded Monterey Jack cheese and shredded sharp Cheddar cheese.
Pan-fry seasoned (oregano, garlic salt and pepper) chicken; shred cooked chicken and place in bowl.
Place 48 nacho chips on cookie sheet.
Evenly distribute shredded chicken on top of nachos.
Spritz with jalapeno juice.
Place 1/2 teaspoon sour cream on top of chicken followed by 1 slice of jalapeno pepper, followed by cheese.
Place in oven at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mrs. jones' pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Mix well.
Alternately add milk and flour.
Add flavorings.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour.
Test with straw.
If not done, cook 15 minutes longer.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Rinse raisins in water, then drain.
Take 2 tablespoons flour and coat raisins.
Sift flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Beat eggs and gradually beat in sugar and oil. With rubber spatula, blend in dry ingredients, alternating with zucchini.
When thoroughly mixed, stir in coated raisins, lemon peel and nuts.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in a 10-inch iron skillet at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until clear and thick.
Cool and pour over fresh strawberries placed in the bottom of pie shell.

title: black-eyed pea jambalaya
directions: In large skillet, saute onion and green pepper in shortening until onion is transparent.
Add meat and ham; simmer.
When meat is cooked medium, add rice and simmer until rice begins to fry, then add water from black-eyed peas and water to equal 2 1/2 cups liquid.
Add to meat at intervals and season, stirring occasionally, until rice is tender, about 40 minutes.
Just before removing from fire, add black-eyed peas; spoon it around in the rice and meat.
You may add onion tops and parsley that have been cut up.

title: matt's banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine and graham cracker crumbs.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1 stick margarine, sugar and eggs.
Beat 5 minutes at medium speed.
Carefully spread on crumbs. Slice bananas over this, then pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with maraschino cherries and chopped nuts.
Refrigerate a few hours or overnight.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Mix together all cake ingredients except marshmallow cream. Bake at 350° in jellyroll pan until done.
While cake is still hot, spread top of cake with marshmallow cream.
Cool.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Put all ingredients in a large mixing bowl; mix.
Put in a freezer can and pour enough milk in to fill a freezer can 3/4 full.

title: easy crust chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender; cool, debone and break or cut into pieces.
Place chicken in an 8 x 11 x 2 inch casserole dish. Sprinkle with pepper.
Mix hot broth and chicken soup, stirring until smooth.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder; mix in softened margarine until crumbly.
Stir in buttermilk.
Pour soup broth mixture over chicken.
Pour the flour mixture over top and bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: polly's italian cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 round cake pans. Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt. Add to egg mixture.
Pour in buttermilk.
Beat well.
Add coconut and pecans.
Mix well.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour batter into prepared pans. Bake for 25 minutes or until center of layers springs back to gentle touch.
Frost with Italian Cream Frosting.

title: poor man steak
directions: Cut up potatoes on bottom of casserole dish.
Cut onion up next.
Put mushroom soup on top of this.
Put flattened-out hamburger on top.
Cook in 475° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Microwave broccoli until thawed; drain. Add mushrooms, water chestnuts and cheese; mix.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. Add onion rings on top and bake 5 minutes or until golden brown and crispy.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix all together and serve with raw vegetables.

title: scampi-style chicken thighs(lo-cal chicken)
directions: Trim excess fat from chicken.
Rinse chicken with cold water. Pat dry.
Place chicken in a shallow container.
Pour lemon juice over chicken and let stand 20 minutes.
Combine parsley and rest of ingredients in a small bowl; stir well.
Spray rack of a broiler pan with Pam.
Remove chicken from lemon juice, discarding lemon juice.
Arrange chicken on rack and brush with parsley mixture. Broil 6 inches from heating element 4 minutes on each side or until tender.
Transfer chicken to a serving platter.
Garnish with lemon wedges and parsley if desired.
Makes 4 servings.
Per serving: 218 calories, 19.4 g protein, 14.3 g fat, 2 g carbohydrates, 70 g cholesterol, 1.1 mg iron, 100 mg sodium, 16 mg calcium.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix together yeast and warm water.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix all dry ingredients and add liquid.
Combine and stir with spoon until blended.
Let rise.
Roll out in desired shape.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix well.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Then refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: christmas breakfast
directions: Crumble bread and mix with grated cheese.
Spread this mixture on the bottom of a 9 x 9-inch Pam sprayed pan. Beat eggs and milk together.
Add salt and pepper and mustard to this mixture.
Pour this mixture over the bread mixture.
Place bacon strips on top of this.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Christmas morning, bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add onion and saute.
In a 1-1/2 qt. dish place a layer of cabbage and a layer of beef.
Sprinkle a little salt, pepper and garlic.
Continue until all cabbage and beef are used, ending with beef.
Pour undiluted tomato soup over top.
Cook covered for 1 hour in 350 degree oven.

title: fish chowder
directions: Cook the salt pork very slowly in a small skillet until fat has melted and the scraps are brown.
Strain, setting aside the crisp scraps and put 2 teaspoons of fat in pot.
Heat.
Add onions and cook over low heat until golden.
Add potatoes; toss until well coated.
Add 4 cups clam juice liquid and minced clams.
Simmer 30 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Cut fish in chunks.
Add to pot.
Simmer partially covered 15 minutes until fish is cooked through.
If using shrimp, add along with shrimp.
Stir in the cream and heat slowly without boiling.
Just before serving, stir in the butter.
Add salt and pepper to taste and heat until the butter melts.

title: treet or spam casserole
directions: Cut Treet meat into chunks or slices.
Place (in a Pyrex dish) a layer of meat, onions, potatoes and cheese.
Cover with with 1/2 the mushroom soup.
Repeat layers.
Cover casserole with 1 soup can of water.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with dinner rolls.

title: ham rolls
directions: Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise, pecans and garlic salt. Spread each slice of ham with mixture.
Roll up in jelly roll fashion.
Chill several hours or freeze one hour.
Slice into pinwheel-like rolls.
Keep refrigerated until serving time.
May be served on Ritz crackers.

title: green rice
directions: Cook rice in 2 cups of water until done. Cook broccoli only slightly and drain.
Saute onion in margarine.
Combine all ingredients, saving some cheese for top. Place in greased casserole and bake uncovered at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken spread
directions: Mix all the items.
Mold into a log.
Chill for 4 hours. Serve with crackers.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Bring to boil.
Put in cucumbers.
Let come to boil and can.

title: grandma lela cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Whip egg and milk together, and add to dry ingredients.
Heat oil in skillet or pan, then add dough. Bake at 400 degrees until done.

title: haystacks
directions: *Meat can be omitted.

title: hamburger lentil soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in skillet.
Combine all ingredients in slow cooker.
Cook on Low for 8 - 10 hours or High for 4 - 6 hours.

title: corned beef-noodle casserole
directions: Do not cook noodles.
Mix all together.
Place in casserole and top with cracker crumb mixture.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken reuben
directions: Drain sauerkraut well.
Press out excess liquid.
Grease baking pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: honey spiced bars
directions: Mix.
Press into greased 11 x 16-inch cookie sheet by hand. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: clam casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Place into greased casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: homemade vegetable beef soup
directions: Place meat, washed bones and 1 1/2 quarts of water in kettle. Simmer 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Remove bones.
Add salt, pepper, cabbage, carrots, string beans, celery and onions; simmer 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Add potatoes, peas, tomatoes, corn, pot herbs and thyme.
Add parsley and pepper.
(Tie parsley and pepper together, if desired, and discard later.)
Simmer 1 hour more.
Yields 8 servings.

title: oat and apple morning muffins
directions: Lightly grease 18 muffin cups or line with paper bake cups; set aside.
Prepare the Streusel Topping.
In a mixing bowl, combine the oats, flour, baking powder, cinnamon and baking soda. In another bowl, stir together the milk, sugar, oil and egg.
Stir in the apples.
Add to the dry ingredients, stirring just until combined.
Stir in raisins.
Fill prepared muffin pan cups with batter.
Sprinkle Streusel Topping over the muffin batter.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 to 18 minutes, or until done.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: mexican salad
directions: Prepare lettuce as for any tossed salad.
Drain and wash beans.
Add diced tomatoes, chopped onion, grated cheese and dressing.
Chill.
Crush Fritos; mix well.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Pare cucumbers.
Slice thin.
Salt them and let stand for 1 hour.
Place liquids in a bowl; dissolve the sugar.
Slice the onions very thin and add finely mashed garlic.
Squeeze out cucumbers from salt; mix with liquids, if desired.
Add 2 tablespoons sour cream.
Sprinkle with black pepper and paprika. Chill.

title: chunky beef stew
directions: Boil stew meat for 2 to 3 hours, or until tender, adding water as needed.
Add carrots and green peppers.
Cook for 15 minutes. Add potatoes, onions, salt and peppers; cook for 20 to 30 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Add tomato sauce.
Heat through.

title: lemon delight
directions: Melt butter and mix with flour and nuts.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Should be lightly golden. Let cool.

title: cheesy green beans
directions: Drain the beans.
Pour the soup over the beans.
Sprinkle with the onion rings. Bake in microwave for 10 minutes on High.

title: three bean hot dish
directions: Fry sausage.
Remove from pan and crumble.
Brown hamburger and add next 5 ingredients.
Cook until blended.
Place all mixture into casserole and bake in a 350 °oven for 40 minutes.

title: blueberry sauce
directions: Simmer fruit and water for 5 minutes.
Mix sugar and cornstarch well.
Stir this dry mixture into simmered fruit.
Cook until thickened.
Serve warm or cold over ice cream, shortcake, etc.

title: fruit salad
directions: Slice bananas.
Put thawed orange juice over them.
Let set for a while.
Mix pudding, using the juice from the pineapple and peaches only.
Combine all ingredients.
Use any kind of fruit you like, using fresh or canned.

title: ritz cracker cookie
directions: Cook together milk and dates on slow heat, stirring constantly. Do not let get hard; take off when together. Add nuts. Spread on Ritz crackers and bake 5 minutes at 250°. Remove and cool.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix sour cream and cream of celery.
Drain corn and beans. Layer corn, beans, pepper, celery and onions in a casserole dish. Spread sour cream and celery soup over vegetables.
Cover with Cheez-Its crackers.
Melt 1 stick margarine and spoon over crackers.
Cook at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind all vegetables and cover with boiling water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Drain.
Add vinegar, sugar and salt.
Boil for 1/2 hour and put into pint jars.

title: peach cream dessert
directions: In saucepan, prepare pudding according to package directions. Drain peaches and arrange slices on pie plate or in shallow mold. Pour cooled pudding over peach slices and chill thoroughly.
Serve with Cool Whip.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: southwest white chili
directions: Mix spices together. Heat oil in large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and onions. Cook 4 to 5 minutes. Stir in broth, green chiles and spice blend. Simmer for 10 minutes. Serve topped with sliced green onions and cheese.

title: kiefer's peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a pan over medium-high heat. Stir constantly until it comes to a full rolling boil.
Boil without stirring until syrup dropped into cool water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat and stir in next 3 ingredients.

title: zucchini pineapple bread(makes two loaves)
directions: In a large bowl, mix together the eggs, sugar, vanilla, oil, and zucchini.
In a separate bowl, mix together the flour, soda, baking powder, and salt.
Add the zucchini batter to the flour batter and mix well.
Stir in raisins, nuts, and pineapple until just blended.
Pour into two 9x5x3-inch loaf pans.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for one hour, or until browned.

title: crispy candy bar cookies
directions: Bring sugar, syrup and peanut butter to a boil.
Remove from heat and mix in crisp rice cereal.
Press into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt together chocolate and butterscotch pieces. Spread over cookies.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Makes 54 cookies.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Shape all ingredients into balls, about 1 1/2 inches in diameter (makes about 16).
Brown in 2 tablespoons shortening. Blend in rest of soup with 1 can of water.
Simmer for about 40 minutes, or until rice is tender.
Stir now and then.
After meat is brown, drain grease and serve.

title: wendy's oatmeal gingersnap cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: bombay appetizer
directions: Whip all ingredients until fluffy.
Mold into disk and chill well.
Before serving, spread with:
1/3 c. mango chutney, 2 Tbsp. flaked coconut, 1/2 c. chopped pecans, 1 Tbsp. green onions, and 1 1/2 Tbsp. currants.

title: sun-sational cheese cake
directions: Combine crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Press onto the bottom of a 9-inch spring pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: my mother's root beer
directions: Put yeast cake in cup of very warm water (not hot).
Let stand.
Put 4 to 4 1/2 gallons of warm water in large container (new clean trash can will do).
Try to keep water warm at all times.
Work quickly.
Add sugar and mix.
Add yeast mixture and mix well.
Add extract.
Pour into bottles.
After each bottle, mix so yeast will distribute (use glass quart bottles for best results).

title: fruit pizza
directions: Line two 12-inch pizza pans with foil.
Spray with Pam cooking spray.
Combine 1/2 cake mix (dry), water, eggs, margarine, and brown sugar in a bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Blend in remaining cake mix.
Fold in nuts.
Divide batter evenly between prepared pans. Bake 15-20 minutes at 350 F. Cool and remove foil.
Spread Cool Whip on top of cake.
Arrange fruit in circular pattern over topping.
Can use strawberries, raspberries, blueberrries, kiwi, bananas, pineapple, grapes, etc.
Brush with apricot glaze.

title: frosted apricot salad
directions: Reserve the liquids from the apricots and pineapple.
Add water to liquid to make 1 1/2 cups.
Reserve a few apricots for garnish.
Chop remaining apricots.
Dissolve the 2 packages Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add measured liquid and chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in fruits.
Pour into 9-inch square pan.
Chill until set, but not firm.
Blend 1/2 cup mayonnaise into 1 cup thawed Cool Whip.
Spread over gelatin.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup Baker's Angel Flake coconut.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Cut into squares and garnish.
Makes 9 servings.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix together well.
Heat Crisco oil (about 1 cup) to 375°. Pour some batter into funnel holding finger over bottom.
Let batter run out of funnel into oil making swirls.
Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with 10x sugar.

title: lumpia
directions: Chop finely the shrimp, onions, carrot, water chestnuts and celery.
Mix first 11 ingredients thoroughly.
Take a heaping tablespoonful and roll in lumpia wrapper.
Make a long roll.
Cut into 2-inch pieces.
Deep fat fry.
Combine the sweet and sour sauce and Tabasco sauce; heat.
Serve with heated sweet and sour sauce in a small bowl.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix together squeezed dry spinach, chopped green onions, chopped celery, chopped eggs and diced cheese.
Add mayonnaise, salt, vinegar and Tabasco sauce.
Refrigerate several hours after serving.
Serves 6.
Temperature should be cool.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Combine sugar, mustard, salt, onion and 1/2 of vinegar.
Beat at second speed with mixer.
Add rest of the vinegar and the oil.

title: whole wheat cottage cheese bread
directions: Combine flour, salt and yeast.
Heat water, honey, butter and cottage cheese to about 110° to 115°.
Add eggs and oatmeal; mix with flour and knead.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down; divide in half.
Place in 2 greased loaf pans; let rise again. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry pie supreme
directions: Thaw shell 10 minutes.
Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Put 1/2 of pie filling over the crust.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°, until crust is brown.
Beat cream cheese, vanilla, eggs and sugar until smooth; pour over hot filling.
Put into reduced oven (350°) for 25 minutes.
Cool completely on wire rack.
After it's cooled, pour remaining pie filling on top.
Put some sour cream or whipped cream around the edge.

title: butterscotch pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
In 1/4 cup hot water, melt 1 cup butterscotch morsels and instant dry coffee.
Add butterscotch mixture to butter and sugar.
Mix remaining dry ingredients and add to batter, alternating with buttermilk.
Add eggs last.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a tube pan.

title: cherry crunch(serves 8)
directions: Cut flour into butter.
Press into
13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Press pecan halves into crust.
Bake
in a 450° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until crunchy.
Cool.

title: freezer dinner rolls
directions: Combine yeast and warm water in a large mixing bowl.
Stir with fork until dissolved and blend in milk, butter, sugar, salt and eggs.
Beat in 2 cups of flour until batter is smooth.
Gradually add sufficient flour to make a soft, workable dough.
Let Kitchen Aid do most of the kneading and use hands toward end to make sure dough is soft and elastic.
Cover with plastic wrap and a towel and let rest for 30 minutes on floured surface.
Punch dough down and shape into desired shapes.
It is a very relaxed and easily molded dough.
Place rolls on greased baking sheets and cover with plastic wrap.
Place in freezer until firm.
Remove and transfer to freezer bags.
When ready to bake, remove rolls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Cover and let rise until doubled, about 2 to 2 1/2 hours. Brush with melted butter and bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mushroom dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except mushrooms and artichokes, and stir over medium heat.
Cook until cheese melts.
Add mushrooms and artichokes last.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: iron skillet chocolate pie
directions: Melt butter in iron skillet.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and cocoa.
Add sugar mixture to melted butter.
Beat egg yolks and add milk and mix well.
Slowly add this to sugar and butter mixture until mixed well.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Pour in baked pie shells.
Beat egg whites and top chocolate mixture.
Brown in oven.
Cool before serving.

title: cake that doesn't last
directions: Mix by hand.
When well blended, pour into a large greased and floured tube or Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook the spaghetti according to package directions; drain. (You should have about 3 1/4 cups cooked spaghetti.) Stir margarine or butter into hot spaghetti. Stir in eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Press spaghetti mixture into a buttered 10-inch microwave-safe pie plate, forming a crust.

In a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole, crumble beef or pork sausage. Add onion and green pepper. Cook, covered, at 100° power (High) for 4 to 6 minutes or until vegetables are tender and meat is no longer pink, stirring once.
Drain off fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, flour, sugar, oregano and garlic salt. Cook, uncovered, on High for 6 to 8 minutes or until bubbly, stirring every 3 minutes. Cook on High for 1 minute more.
Cover and set aside.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and green pepper.
Put everything together in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with corn meal mix (mixed according to directions) and bake at 350° until done.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix ingredients all in bowl.
Drop on greased cookie sheet by spoonfuls and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla, milk and flour.
Mix well.
Drop or roll out and bake about 12 minutes in 300° oven.
Do not overcook.

title: grilled pork tenderloin
directions: Preheat gas grill on high temperature.
Wash pork tenderloin and dry well.
Season with pepper.
Place on grill; sear meat on all sides.
Reduce to low heat.
Brush meat with margarine; turn frequently.
Cook until internal temperature of meat is 180°. Serve meat with side dish of sauce that has been heated.

title: chocolate cinnamon bars
directions: Sift
together
flour, baking powder, 1 cup sugar and 3 teaspoons cinnamon.
Add
margarine,
shortening,
1 egg and 1 egg yolk.
Blend well with wooden spoon or mixer on low speed. Turn into
a
lightly
greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread evenly with spatula.
Beat
egg
white
slightly;
brush over batter. Combine remaining
cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, chocolate bits and nuts;
sprinkle
over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: melt in your mouth chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken with water, 1/2 stick margarine, salt and pepper. Cool. Cut into small pieces. Place in a 9 x 13 inch casserole dish. In a bowl mix soups and chicken broth, mix until smooth. Pour over chicken. Prepare topping: mix flour, buttermilk, and 2 sticks of melted margarine. Stir until well blended. Pour over chicken. Bake at 425° for 30-45 minutes.

title: easy potato chowder
directions: Saute bacon and onion until bacon begins to crisp; remove excess bacon grease, if desired.
Add milk, broth and thyme; bring to a boil.
Stir in potatoes; simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in parsley, salt and pepper.
Makes 6 servings, each with 175 calories, 14 g fat and 24 mg cholesterol.

title: okra and tomato casserole
directions: Heat shortening in a large skillet.
Add okra; saute until tender.
Add tomatoes and corn; simmer for 5 minutes.
Add sausage, salt and pepper; stir well.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes. May be eaten over rice or alone.

title: candied carrots (lo-cal)
directions: Place all ingredients in saucepan; cover and bring to a boil. Simmer slowly for about 25 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit, saving 1 1/2 c. of the pineapple juice. Combine fruit and marshmallows. Soften gelatin in cold water. Heat pineapple juice to boiling. Add gelatin and stir to dissolve. Add orange and lemon juices, sugar and salt. Stir to dissolve. Chill. When mixture starts to thicken, add fruit mixture and nuts. Fold in Cool Whip and salad dressing. Spoon into quart containers and freeze. Makes 9 quarts.

title: green corn pudding
directions: With sharp knife cut through center of kernels; scrape cob. Measure 1 1/4 cups corn.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Stir corn, sugar, butter and salt.
Slowly beat in milk. Fold in egg whites.
Bake in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish at 350° until knife inserted off center comes out clean, 45 to 50 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook until thick, about 40 minutes.
Put into jars and seal. Makes 6 quarts.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake for 6 hours at 250°.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and roll into small balls. Chill 1 hour.

title: nacho dip
directions: Line casserole pan evenly with salsa; cover.
Brown hamburger. Add taco seasoning and chopped jalapeno pepper.
Add to hamburger.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Add chili mix and simmer.
Cover salsa with hamburger; cover this with cheese.
Microwave 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir and top with second bag of Cheddar cheese.
Goes good with any type of chips.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in small amount of boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain well and combine all ingredients except 1/4 cup cheese and crushed crackers.
Place in baking dish and spread remaining cheese and crackers over top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly or about 25 minutes.

title: unbaked chocolate clusters
directions: Place sugar, milk and butter in saucepan and bring to a rolling boil.
Boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients in a bowl and pour boiling mixture over the top.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Cool.

title: patty's goulash
directions: Brown meat in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Stir in herb spice mix from Kraft Italian style spaghetti dinner, tomatoes, tomato paste and water.
Cover.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: kugel(noodle pudding)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as directed on package and drain. Put back into large pot.
Add all of the ingredients except brown sugar.
Add sugar until desired sweetness.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch baking pan (ungreased).
Bake for one hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: florida chiffon pie
directions: Mix gelatin, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Beat egg yolks, lime and orange juice and water; stir into gelatin mixture.
Cook and stir just until mixture boils.
Remove from heat; cool to room temperature and stir in peel.
Chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when spooned.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks.
Slowly add remaining 1/2 cup sugar, beating to stiff peaks. Fold in gelatin mixture.
Pile into baked, cooled 9-inch pastry shell.
Chill until firm.
Serve with whipped cream (good without the cream, too).
This makes a very high pie!

title: reuben casserole
directions: Combine noodles, meat and marinade.
Mix lightly.
Spoon into 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Combine sauerkraut, dressing and caraway; mix lightly.
Spoon over noodle mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with croutons and cheese.
Continue baking 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix well.
Place 2 inches apart on well-greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool.

title: trifle
directions: Slice strawberries and bananas into thin slices.
Break angel food cake into small pieces.
Cover bottom of a large glass bowl with cake.
Layer bananas, strawberries and pudding.
Start over with cake again.
Finally, top with Cool Whip and garnish with sliced strawberries.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: bessie's hot rolls
directions: Put yeast in cup and put 2 Tbsp cold water over yeast; stir until dissolved and set aside.
Cream together Crisco, sugar and salt in mixing bowl.
Add
the boiling water; stir until Crisco mixture has melted.
Let cool until Crisco begins to harden.
Add yeast to mixture; rinse cup with one cup cold water and add to the mixture.
Add 5 cups flour and mix well.
Cover, and put in refrigerator.
Use as desired to make rolls of your choice - Parker house, clover leaf, etc.
Let rise 2-3 hours.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: shrimp batter
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Dip shrimp and fry.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix the first nine ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread dry yellow or white cake mix on top. Sprinkle with nuts and drizzle oleo over all.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 50 minutes.

title: "frog eyes"(fruit tapioca)
directions: Put tapioca and water in a 4-quart pan.
Cover.
Let soak 3 hours.
You might have to add more water.
Cook tapioca and water over low/medium heat (until most of the tapioca is soft and transparent.
You want some white tapioca).
Stir constantly.
Turn off heat.
Add box of jello.
Stir well.
Remove from heat.
Add fruit and stir.
Put into clear glass bowl and serve.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate to chill.

title: confetti corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Break eggs into mixing bowl and beat well.
Melt margarine. Combine eggs, margarine, corn, pimentos, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish and top with onion rings.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti shells; drain and set aside.
Cook spinach; drain and squeeze out excess liquid.
Combine spinach, cottage cheese, Parmesan, pepper and garlic.
Stuff shells and arrange in a 9 x 13-inch pan coated with vegetable spray.
Pour tomato sauce over manicotti.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon cake top pudding
directions: Add ingredients in order given, adding butter to milk.
Fold in egg whites and cook in covered casserole in pan of water 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order given.
Put in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.
Sift powdered sugar on top.

title: navy bean and cashew salad
directions: Marinate together first 4 ingredients.
Toss with lettuce or mixed greens and cashews.
Top with Avocado Dressing.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients until strings form a hard ball.
Add raw peanuts with skins.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes on medium heat. Stir.
Take off heat and add, at once, the soda and salt.
Spread on buttered foil paper.
When cool, break in pieces.

title: filled cupcakes
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed. Fill cupcake tins 1/2 full (can use paper or foil cupcake papers).
If not, grease pan well. Combine the cream cheese, sugar, egg and chocolate chips. Add 1 teaspoon of the mixture to the cake mix in the pan.

title: raisin pie
directions: Bake in an 8-inch pie shell for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook the frozen vegetables, onion and green pepper together. Mix all ingredients and put in a large baking dish. Top with buttered crumbs, if desired.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°. Uncover and bake another 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: garlic lime chicken
directions: In a bowl, mix together first 7 ingredients.
Evenly sprinkle mixture on both sides of chicken breasts.

title: pecan cream pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and cook until thickened. Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and brown.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix ingredients. Setting overnight helps flavors mix, but is not required.

title: peanut butter-chocolate bars
directions: Combine all ingredients until smooth.
Press mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Push hard.
Melt chocolate chips and pour over top.
Refrigerate until chocolate hardens.
Remove and cut.
Serve at room temperature.

title: peach pudding
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and bake in a round baking dish for approximately 30 minutes until hot.
Take from oven. Beat the egg whites until stiff, then gradually add sugar until glossy.
Spread this over the peach mixture and return to oven for about 14 minutes, until meringue has browned.

title: quick mexican dish
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain off fat.
Add taco seasoning and corn; mix well.
In separate bowl, mix soups, tomatoes and chilies together.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground chuck in a deep pan and pour off any grease.
Add jars of Pizza Quick and stir.
Next, add eggs, Ricotta and Parmesan cheese; blend together.

title: pizza loaf
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a loaf pan.
In mixing bowl, stir together all ingredients, except pepperoni, until moistened.
Stir in pepperoni.
Spread mixture in pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 5 minutes and remove from pan.
Cool 20 minutes.

title: old-time rice pudding
directions: Wash rice.
Add milk, sugar, nutmeg and salt.
Place in a buttered 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours, stirring twice during the first hour.
Stir brown crust into pudding several times during remainder of baking.
Add raisins 1/2 hour before pudding is done, then allow crust to form again on pudding.

title: summer cooler
directions: Combine ingredients in blender and blend until well mixed.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 400° until done as you would any other bread.

title: oatmeal choc-chip pecan cookies
directions: Mix sugars, oleo, add baking powder, soda, then eggs, flour, vanilla, salt; mix well. Then add oatmeal, choc-chips and pecans. Drop on greased pan, bake at 350° until light brown.

title: pecan pie - never fail
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 35 minutes.

title: pasta and sauteed garlic
directions: Peel and thinly slice garlic.
Cook spaghetti al dente; drain. Saute garlic in olive oil until slightly golden.
Immediately stir into spaghetti.
Add Parmesan, salt and pepper to taste.

title: prayer bars
directions: Combine 1/2 cup butter, sugar, cocoa and vanilla in double boiler and cook until blended.
Add egg and cook 5 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add coconut, graham crackers and nuts.
Pat into buttered 9 x 13-inch cookie pan. Spread with mixture of 1/2 cup soft butter, milk, pudding mix and powdered sugar.
Cool in refrigerator.
Melt chocolate chips and 2 tablespoons butter.
Spread on 2nd layer.
Cut in squares and store in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oats, water and margarine; let stand for 20 minutes. Cream sugar and eggs; add oat mixture and dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Turn into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, pickle relish and pickle juice.
Stir until well blended.
In a clear bowl, layer as follows: 1/2 crumbled cornbread, 1/2 tomatoes, 1/2 green pepper, 1/2 onion, 1/2 jar bacon bits and 1/2 dressing.
Repeat layers and refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: almond butter
directions: Blend softened margarine with almonds, honey and cinnamon. Place in covered container.
Can be kept in refrigerator for up to 3 weeks.
Especially good on banana bread or pumpkin bread.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy cabbage roll casserole
directions: Brown meat to which onion has been added. In a greased baking dish (9 x 13), layer cabbage, meat and rice. Mix soup, sauce and water together. Pour over
cabbage mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: macaroni and tomato bake
directions: In a bowl, combine macaroni, tomatoes, onion (minced fine), pepper, sweet basil and 1 1/2 cups shredded cheese.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except Cheddar cheese.
Place mixture into casserole dish and bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese and bake for 10 more minutes.

title: make your own crust chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken and take meat off the bone.
Place it in a dish. Then mix up chicken soup and chicken broth.
Pour over chicken. Drain vegetables and spread over chicken and soup mixture before spooning on crust.

title: fruit salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; cool.
Add sherbet; cool until slightly thickened.
Add fruit; allow to congeal.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: tomato juice cocktail
directions: Cook tomatoes.
Strain tomatoes; add salt, sugar, celery salt, onion salt and garlic salt.
Bring to boil and can.

title: peppermint crunches
directions: Put milk, sugar and syrup in saucepan.
Cook until mixture boils and is bubbly on top.
Boil and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips, stirring until melted.
Cool 10 minutes.
Add candy and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop onto waxed paper and chill.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour well to remove any lumps.
Stir in milk and beaten egg yolks.
Cook pudding over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Layer pudding, wafers and bananas, making two layers.
End with the pudding.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/4 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon at a time until stiff but not dry.
Add 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla.
Pour meringue over pudding, spreading to edge.
Bake at 450° until meringue is golden brown.

title: barbecue biscuit cups
directions: Brown beef; drain fat.
Add salt and barbecue sauce; simmer gently about 15 minutes.
Grease 10 muffin cups.
Place 1 biscuit in each cup, shaping with fingers to fit muffin cup.
Spoon meat mixture into biscuit cups, filling about 3/4 full.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: cherry whip dessert
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and melted margarine; spread in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix Dream Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Spread over graham cracker mixture, then spread cherry pie filling on this and chill.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Fry sausage; drain.
Mix other ingredients together in 2-quart dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, then at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add eggs, oil and buttermilk; mix until blended.
May be stored in covered container in refrigerator for as long as 4 weeks.
Bake as needed in lightly greased muffin cups at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: golden fruit salad
directions: Mix together sugar, cornstarch mixture, lemon juice and orange juice.
Stir and boil 1 minute.
Pour hot mixture over fruit. Leave uncovered until cool.
Makes a large bowl.
Will feed 10 to 12 people.

title: truffles
directions: Grind nuts in blender.
Line bottom of 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with waxed paper.
In heavy saucepan, combine heavy cream and chocolate.
Heat over low heat just until chocolate is melted. Remove from heat.
In medium bowl, combine nuts, powdered sugar and egg white.
Stir with wooden spoon until combined.
Stir in chocolate mixture and rum to combine well.
Turn into loaf pan. Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 3/4-inch squares; shape in balls.
Roll in chocolate sprinkles.
Store in refrigerator. Yields 60.

title: scrabble
directions: Mix in dishpan or garbage bag the cereals, pecans and pretzels.
Mix spices together in a bowl and pour over cereal. Put in pan to cook.
Slice oleo over mixture and pour oil over it. Cook at 225° for 4 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and margarine in saucepan; cook on high until margarine melts and mixture is hot. Mix slowly with beaten eggs, stirring constantly. Add pecans and vanilla. Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes (until it doesn't shake in middle).

title: holiday salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into a mold or any type Pyrex dish. Chill or freeze as desired or it can be eaten immediately.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix well. May add nuts, if desired. Serve with sliced apples. Good with Granny Smith apples.

title: lemon ice cream pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and 1 egg white together.
Add salt, sugar and lemon juice. Cook in double boiler until thick (cool).
Beat and add the two remaining egg whites.
Whip the cream and add.
Place half of the vanilla wafers in refrigerator tray. Add lemon mixture and top with remaining vanilla wafers. Freeze.
Cut and serve with whipped cream and cherries.

title: mrs. williams' chuck roast
directions: Use a heavy skillet with cover.
Melt margarine.
Place meat in pan.
Pour vinegar over the roast, cover and cook over low heat (250°).
Keep turning every 15 minutes.
Keep covered.
Do not add water!
Cook until fork-tender, approximately 3 hours.
Can add potatoes the last 45 minutes.
You won't believe it!

title: spicy apple warm-up
directions: In large pan, combine all ingredients.
Mix well and heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot in warm mugs.
Garnish with orange and lemon slices.
Use cinnamon sticks as stirrers. Can be prepared in large bowl in microwave.
Serve 12 (1/2-cup servings).

title: french fried almond shrimp
directions: Peel shrimp without removing tail and last joint of tail. Remove vein.
Combine dry ingredients; coat shrimp.
Chill. Combine eggs and oil.
Dip shrimp in egg mixture, then into almonds.
Fry in hot oil (375°) for 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve with your choice of soy sauce, duck sauce and/or melted butter.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: In large skillet over medium heat in hot margarine cook onions, celery and carrots until tender, stirring occasionally. Stir in beef; heat through.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add beef broth, stirring constantly.
Heat to boiling.
Stir in Worcestershire.
Spoon mixture into 1 1/2-quart round casserole. Top with mashed potatoes.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 4.

title: sugar and spice donuts
directions: Combine flours, soda, baking powder, salt and nutmeg in bowl. Beat together buttermilk, egg sugar; add this to the first mixture along with melted butter; mixing until a soft dough forms.
Turn out onto a floured surface; knead lightly.
Pat and roll dough to 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut with floured cutter.
Fry donuts and holes in hot oil, 375 degrees, turning once and frying 3 minutes on each side. Drain on paper towels.
While hot, dip in the cinnamon sugar.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in olive oil until golden brown.
Remove from pan and set aside.
Saute onion in olive oil until soft, but not brown.
Add tomato sauce, garlic powder, bay leaf and spices. When well blended, add chicken back.
Bring to a boil slowly; lower heat.
Add wine; cover and simmer for one hour.
Serve with rice, white preferred.

title: caramel bars
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients in double boiler and keep warm.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended, reserving 2 ounces of Blue cheese.
Once all is well blended, add Blue cheese in chunks and stir in the cheese.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: *We stew the wings and giblets from turkey for dressing and bake the turkey.

title: teddi's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix well.
Put into 9-inch unbaked pastry shell.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 325°.
Add Cool Whip as desired.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Combine half of peaches and 1/4 cup milk in blender.
Process until smooth.
Transfer to a bowl and repeat procedure with remaining peaches and 1/4 cup milk.
Set aside.
Combine remaining 2 1/2 cups milk and next 3 ingredients.
Heat 1 1/2 cups milk with sugar until sugar is melted.
Cool.
After milk is cool, add remaining ingredients.
Pour into container of 4-quart electric freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: deer pie
directions: Place deer, celery, onion and peppers in skillet and fry until meat browns well.
Add the remaining items and cook until onion, peppers and celery are soft.
Turn into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell, then top with another pie shell and seal edges.
Place slits in top of shell for steam to escape.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: heavenly fudge sauce
directions: Combine the powdered sugar, chocolate morsels, butter, evaporated milk and salt in medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, for 15 to 20 minutes, or until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Let cool.
Transfer sauce to a serving bowl.
Serve with fresh fruit and pound cake cubes or over ice cream.

title: sugared twists
directions: Soften yeast in warm water and set aside.
Into mixing bowl, sift together flour and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Mix in sour cream, vanilla and yeast.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir until thoroughly blended.
Cover and chill for at least 3 hours.
Sprinkle several tablespoons of sugar on board and place dough on sugar.
Roll into 12-inch square.
Fold dough over at ends to measure 12 x 4-inches, working quickly.
Re-roll in similar way three to six times more, using 2 to 4 tablespoons sugar each time.
The last time roll dough 1/4-inch.
Brush with egg white and sprinkle with remaining sugar.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes.
Cool and slice.
Brown bacon.
Remove bits from pan and to the drippings; add flour, onion and celery.
Saute 1 minute.
Add sugar, water and vinegar.
Cook, stirring until clear and glossy.
Toss all ingredients.

title: st. patrick's potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Beat the cream cheese with electric mixer until smooth.
Add potatoes and remaining ingredients, except paprika.
Beat just until combined.
Spoon mixture into buttered casserole (or use Pam).
Sprinkle paprika; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove and uncover for 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ranchero beans
directions: Clean beans by rinsing.
In large pan, cover with water.
Add taco seasoning, garlic, bouillon, onion, salt, cumin and pepper. Bring to a boil, then lower to medium heat and cook for 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Add water occasionally, if necessary.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into large Pyrex dish which has been greased.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: miniature ham and cheese rolls
